Title: 1. The Shawshank Redemption
Short Description: A banker convicted of uxoricide forms a friendship over a quarter century with a hardened convict, while maintaining his innocence and trying to remain hopeful through simple compassion.

Title: 2. Attack on Titan the Movie: The Last Attack
Short Description: The fate of the world hangs in the balance as Eren unleashes the ultimate power of the Titans. With a burning determination to eliminate all who threaten Eldia, he leads an unstoppable army of Colossal Titans towards Marley.

Title: 3. The Godfather
Short Description: The aging patriarch of an organized crime dynasty transfers control of his clandestine empire to his reluctant son.

Title: 4. Ramayana: The Legend of Prince Rama
Short Description: An anime adaptation of the Hindu epic the Ramayana, where Lord Ram combats the wicked king Ravana.

Title: 5. The Chaos Class
Short Description: Lazy, uneducated students share a very close bond. They live together in the dormitory, where they plan their latest pranks. When a new headmaster arrives, the students naturally try to overthrow him. A comic war of nitwits follows.

Title: 6. The Dark Knight
Short Description: When a menace known as the Joker wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham, Batman, James Gordon and Harvey Dent must work together to put an end to the madness.

Title: 7. Schindler's List
Short Description: In German-occupied Poland during World War II, industrialist Oskar Schindler gradually becomes concerned for his Jewish workforce after witnessing their persecution by the Nazis.

Title: 8. The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King
Short Description: Gandalf and Aragorn lead the World of Men against Sauron's army to draw his gaze from Frodo and Sam as they approach Mount Doom with the One Ring.

Title: 9. 12 Angry Men
Short Description: The jury in a New York City murder trial is frustrated by a single member whose skeptical caution forces them to more carefully consider the evidence before jumping to a hasty verdict.

Title: 10. The Godfather Part II
Short Description: The early life and career of Vito Corleone in 1920s New York City is portrayed, while his son, Michael, expands and tightens his grip on the family crime syndicate.

Title: 11. The Silence of Swastika
Short Description: Hitler used a symbol for his political and racial ideology. The world today calls that symbol "Swastika", an Indian name to a symbol used by Hindus, Buddhists, and Jains for ages. But was it a Swastika? or Something else?

Title: 12. I'm Still Here
Short Description: A woman married to a former politician during the military dictatorship in Brazil is forced to chart a new path for herself and her children after her family's life is impacted by a violent and arbitrary act.

Title: 13. The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring
Short Description: A meek Hobbit from the Shire and eight companions set out on a journey to destroy the powerful One Ring and save Middle-earth from the Dark Lord Sauron.

Title: 14. Pulp Fiction
Short Description: The lives of two mob hitmen, a boxer, a gangster and his wife, and a pair of diner bandits intertwine in four tales of violence and redemption.

Title: 15. O.J.: Made in America
Short Description: A chronicle of the rise and fall of O.J. Simpson, whose high-profile murder trial exposed the extent of American racial tensions, revealing a fractured and divided nation.

Title: 16. The Message
Short Description: The story of prophet "Muhammad" and the delivery of the message of God "Allah."

Title: 17. Tosun Pasha
Short Description: In a battle for the "Green Valley", long-standing Turkish rival families Seferoglu and Tellioglu compete. Daver Bey, father of the lovely Leyla, holds the key as both families pursue her hand in marriage.

Title: 18. Mirror Game
Short Description: A struggling actor becomes a professional impostor, hired to impersonate people for financial gain, but as he delves deeper into his work he becomes embroiled in trouble that threatens to unravel his life.

Title: 19. Inception
Short Description: A thief who steals corporate secrets through the use of dream-sharing technology is given the inverse task of planting an idea into the mind of a C.E.O., but his tragic past may doom the project and his team to disaster.

Title: 20. Fight Club
Short Description: An insomniac office worker and a devil-may-care soap maker form an underground fight club that evolves into much more.

Title: 21. Forrest Gump
Short Description: The history of the United States from the 1950s to the '70s unfolds from the perspective of an Alabama man with an IQ of 75, who yearns to be reunited with his childhood sweetheart.

Title: 22. The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers
Short Description: While Frodo and Sam edge closer to Mordor with the help of the shifty Gollum, the divided fellowship makes a stand against Sauron's new ally, Saruman, and his hordes of Isengard.

Title: 23. The Good, the Bad and the Ugly
Short Description: A bounty-hunting scam joins two men in an uneasy alliance against a third in a race to find a fortune in gold buried in a remote cemetery.

Title: 24. 12th Fail
Short Description: The real-life story of IPS Officer Manoj Kumar Sharma and IRS Officer Shraddha Joshi.

Title: 25. The Phantom of the Opera at the Royal Albert Hall
Short Description: A disfigured musical genius, hidden away in the Paris Opera House, terrorizes the opera company for the unwitting benefit of a young protégée whom he trains and loves.

Title: 26. Balkan Spy
Short Description: Convinced that his subtenant is a spy and an enemy of the state, a man falls into deep paranoia which leads to absurd and destructive chain of events.

Title: 27. #Home
Short Description: Oliver Twist (Indrans) wants to be tech-savvy and become a better companion to his two sons, who spend more time on their phones than with their loved ones.

Title: 28. Maratonci trce pocasni krug
Short Description: The Topalovic family has been in the burial business for generations. When the old (150 yrs old) Pantelija dies, five generations of his heirs start to fight for the inheritance.

Title: 29. The Chaos Class Failed the Class
Short Description: A young and beautiful female teacher starts working in an all boys high school.

Title: 30. The Foster Brothers
Short Description: Saban, Ramazan and Bayram are sailors in an Ottoman Navy and Hüsamettin is their commander. Hüsamettin's aide Ramazan, Saban who is foster son of Hüsamettin's sister and Bayram who is married to Hüsamettin's niece stays at Hüsamettin's family residence.

Title: 31. Interstellar
Short Description: When Earth becomes uninhabitable in the future, a farmer and ex-NASA pilot, Joseph Cooper, is tasked to pilot a spacecraft, along with a team of researchers, to find a new planet for humans.

Title: 32. The Matrix
Short Description: When a beautiful stranger leads computer hacker Neo to a forbidding underworld, he discovers the shocking truth--the life he knows is the elaborate deception of an evil cyber-intelligence.

Title: 33. Goodfellas
Short Description: The story of Henry Hill and his life in the mafia, covering his relationship with his wife Karen and his mob partners Jimmy Conway and Tommy DeVito.

Title: 34. One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest
Short Description: In the Fall of 1963, a Korean War veteran and criminal pleads insanity and is admitted to a mental institution, where he rallies up the scared patients against the tyrannical nurse.

Title: 35. Star Wars: Episode V - The Empire Strikes Back
Short Description: After the Empire overpowers the Rebel Alliance, Luke Skywalker begins his Jedi training with Yoda. At the same time, Darth Vader and bounty hunter Boba Fett pursue his friends across the galaxy.

Title: 36. Jai Bhim
Short Description: When a tribal man is arrested for a case of alleged theft, his wife turns to a human-rights lawyer to help bring justice.

Title: 37. Kill Bill: The Whole Bloody Affair
Short Description: The Bride must kill her ex-boss and lover Bill who betrayed her at her wedding rehearsal, shot her in the head and took away her unborn daughter. But first, she must make the other four members of the Deadly Viper Assassination Squad suffer.

Title: 38. Stop Making Sense
Short Description: A live performance of the band Talking Heads shot over the course of three nights at Hollywood's Pantages Theater in December of 1983 and featuring their most memorable songs.

Title: 39. Shoah
Short Description: Claude Lanzmann's epic documentary recounts the story of the Holocaust through interviews with witnesses - perpetrators as well as survivors.

Title: 40. Soorarai Pottru
Short Description: Inspired by the book 'Simply Fly', the film tells the story of Nedumaaran Rajangam known to friends as Maara, the son of a teacher, who sets out to make the common man fly and takes on the most capital intensive industry in the world with the help of his friends, family and sheer will power.

Title: 41. 777 Charlie
Short Description: Dharma is stuck in a rut with his negative and lonely lifestyle and spends each day in the comfort of his loneliness. A pup named Charlie enters his life and gives him a new perspective towards it.

Title: 42. Toma
Short Description: Biopic about Toma Zdravkovic, the man who is remembered not only for his songs and the unique way he sang them, but also as a bohemian, both in his behavior and his soul.

Title: 43. Rocketry: The Nambi Effect
Short Description: The story of Indian Space Research Organization scientist Nambi Narayanan, who was framed for being a spy and arrested in 1994.

Title: 44. Nayakan
Short Description: A common man's struggles against a corrupt police force put him on the wrong side of the law. He becomes a don, who is loved and respected by many, but his growing power and influence exact a heavy toll.

Title: 45. Pariyerum Perumal
Short Description: A law student from a lower caste begins a friendship with his classmate, a girl who belongs to a higher caste, and the men in her family start giving him trouble over this.

Title: 46. Saban, Son of Saban
Short Description: Husamettin the commander in the army is constantly bothered by the stupidity of one of his soldiers Saban. After discharge from the army, Saban and his friend Ramazan work in a night club as member of the band. They ran again into Husamettin and his in laws, but things gets complicated when the diamond of the family is been stolen.

Title: 47. Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba - Mt. Natagumo Arc
Short Description: Tanjiro teams up with Zenitsu and Inosuke to investigate missing person cases on the mountain Natagumo. They slowly begin to realize the entire mountain is being controlled by a family of Demon spider creatures.

Title: 48. Who's Singin' Over There?
Short Description: It's April 5, 1941, somewhere in Serbia. A group of people go on a bus to Belgrade, on a journey that will change their lives forever.

Title: 49. Resurrection
Short Description: A single father tries to raise his daughter, who has cerebral palsy, even as she is beginning to wake up to her sexuality.

Title: 50. Feyzo, the Polite One
Short Description: A poor peasant, Feyzo returns from military service dreaming about getting married to Gülo, the love of his life. However, he has to face many obstacles. According to tradition, a man has to pay a lot of money to the bride's father in order to get the bride's hand.

Title: 51. Manichithrathazhu
Short Description: When a forbidden room in an old bungalow is unbolted, the spirit of a vengeful dancer is unleashed.

Title: 52. Happy Days
Short Description: A mid-aged couple with 6 kids who are running a pickle shop gets divorced with 3 kids each. The family members find each other years later with a funny story.

Title: 53. The Chaos Class Is Waking Up
Short Description: A kind and hardworking student joins to Hababam Sinifi (The Chaos Class) but they don't accept him as one of them and he becomes the target of all class' pranks.

Title: 54. Se7en
Short Description: Two detectives, a rookie and a veteran, hunt a serial killer who uses the seven deadly sins as his motives.

Title: 55. Saving Private Ryan
Short Description: Following the Normandy Landings, a group of U.S. soldiers go behind enemy lines to retrieve a paratrooper whose brothers have been killed in action.

Title: 56. The Silence of the Lambs
Short Description: A young F.B.I. cadet must receive the help of an incarcerated and manipulative cannibal killer to help catch another serial killer, a madman who skins his victims.

Title: 57. The Green Mile
Short Description: Paul Edgecomb, the head death row guard at a prison in 1930s Louisiana, meets an inmate, John Coffey, a black man who is accused of murdering two girls. His life changes drastically when he discovers that John has a special gift.

Title: 58. Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope
Short Description: Luke Skywalker joins forces with a Jedi Knight, a cocky pilot, a Wookiee and two droids to save the galaxy from the Empire's world-destroying battle station, while also attempting to rescue Princess Leia from the mysterious Darth Vader.

Title: 59. City of God
Short Description: In the slums of Rio, two kids' paths diverge as one struggles to become a photographer and the other a kingpin.

Title: 60. Terminator 2: Judgment Day
Short Description: A cyborg, identical to the one who failed to kill Sarah Connor, must now protect her ten year old son John from an even more advanced and powerful cyborg.

Title: 61. Spirited Away
Short Description: During her family's move to the suburbs, a sullen 10-year-old girl wanders into a world ruled by gods, witches and spirits, and where humans are changed into beasts.

Title: 62. Life Is Beautiful
Short Description: When an open-minded Jewish waiter and his son become victims of the Holocaust, he uses a perfect mixture of will, humor and imagination to protect his son from the dangers around their camp.

Title: 63. It's a Wonderful Life
Short Description: An angel is sent from Heaven to help a desperately frustrated businessman by showing him what life would have been like if he had never existed.

Title: 64. Seven Samurai
Short Description: Farmers from a village exploited by bandits hire a veteran samurai for protection, and he gathers six other samurai to join him.

Title: 65. Harakiri
Short Description: When a ronin requesting seppuku at a feudal lord's palace is told of the brutal suicide of another ronin who previously visited, he reveals how their pasts are intertwined - and in doing so challenges the clan's integrity.

Title: 66. Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba - Tsuzumi Mansion Arc
Short Description: Tanjiro ventures to the south-southeast where he encounters a cowardly young man named Zenitsu Agatsuma. He is a fellow survivor from Final Selection and his sparrow asks Tanjiro to help keep him in line.

Title: 67. A Dog's Will
Short Description: The lively João Grilo and the sly Chicó are poor guys living in the hinterland who cheat a bunch of people to survive, but their plans are halted when a bandit comes to town.

Title: 68. Earthlings
Short Description: Using hidden cameras and never-before-seen footage, Earthlings chronicles the day-to-day practices of the largest industries in the world, all of which rely entirely on animals for profit.

Title: 69. The Legend of Maula Jatt
Short Description: From times untold where legends are written in soil with blood, a hero is born. Maula Jatt, a fierce prizefighter with a tortured past seeks vengeance against his arch nemesis Noori Natt, the most feared warrior in the land of Punjab.

Title: 70. Anbe Sivam
Short Description: Two men, one young and arrogant, the other damaged - physically but not spiritually - by life, are thrown together by circumstances, and find that they are in some ways bound together by fate.

Title: 71. Pretty Village, Pretty Flame
Short Description: During the war in Bosnia, two childhood friends eventually become enemies, as the tragic and devastating circumstances of the war put them on the opposite sides and expose the most gruesome and cruel aspects of the human nature.

Title: 72. My Dear Brother
Short Description: Two poor men try to find a television as a last wish for the terminally ill brother of one of them.

Title: 73. Daman
Short Description: The film is set in 2015. Sid, is a young doctor who completed his MBBS has been posted to the cut-off area of Malkangiri district Odisha having 151 villages & infamous for Naxals dominance & no basic facilities. It's a real life tale of perseverance & dedication.

Title: 74. The Broken Landlord
Short Description: The landlord of a village in eastern Turkey decides to sell his land after a severe drought and migrates to Istanbul with his family. However the struggle for survival in the 'big city' will not be easier for them.

Title: 75. The Chaos Class Is on Vacation
Short Description: Hababam Sinifi (The Chaos Class) continue to their adventures. Now first female students of the school history joins to the class and all Hababam Sinifi fight each other for them at first but later they understand that female students are trouble as much as Hababam Sinifi and played with them so they decide to fight against that girls.

Title: 76. Gladiator
Short Description: A former Roman General sets out to exact vengeance against the corrupt emperor who murdered his family and sent him into slavery.

Title: 77. Dune: Part Two
Short Description: Paul Atreides unites with the Fremen while on a warpath of revenge against the conspirators who destroyed his family. Facing a choice between the love of his life and the fate of the universe, he endeavors to prevent a terrible future.

Title: 78. Parasite
Short Description: Greed and class discrimination threaten the newly formed symbiotic relationship between the wealthy Park family and the destitute Kim clan.

Title: 79. Alien
Short Description: After investigating a mysterious transmission of unknown origin, the crew of a commercial spacecraft encounters a deadly lifeform.

Title: 80. The Prestige
Short Description: Rival 19th-century magicians engage in a bitter battle for trade secrets.

Title: 81. The Departed
Short Description: An undercover cop and a mole in the police attempt to identify each other while infiltrating an Irish gang in South Boston.

Title: 82. The Lion King
Short Description: Lion prince Simba and his father are targeted by his bitter uncle, who wants to ascend the throne himself.

Title: 83. Léon: The Professional
Short Description: 12-year-old Mathilda is reluctantly taken in by Léon, a professional assassin, after her family is murdered. An unusual relationship forms as she becomes his protégée and learns the assassin's trade.

Title: 84. Whiplash
Short Description: A promising young drummer enrolls at a cut-throat music conservatory where his dreams of greatness are mentored by an instructor who will stop at nothing to realize a student's potential.

Title: 85. The Usual Suspects
Short Description: The sole survivor of a pier shoot-out tells the story of how a notorious criminal influenced the events that began with five criminals meeting in a seemingly random police lineup.

Title: 86. Django Unchained
Short Description: With the help of a German bounty-hunter, a freed slave sets out to rescue his wife from a brutal plantation owner in Mississippi.

Title: 87. Back to the Future
Short Description: Marty McFly, a 17-year-old high school student, is accidentally sent 30 years into the past in a time-traveling DeLorean invented by his close friend, the maverick scientist Doc Brown.

Title: 88. Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse
Short Description: Miles Morales catapults across the multiverse, where he encounters a team of Spider-People charged with protecting its very existence. When the heroes clash on how to handle a new threat, Miles must redefine what it means to be a hero.

Title: 89. The Pianist
Short Description: During WWII, acclaimed Polish musician Wladyslaw faces various struggles as he loses contact with his family. As the situation worsens, he hides in the ruins of Warsaw in order to survive.

Title: 90. American History X
Short Description: Living a life marked by violence, neo-Nazi Derek finally goes to prison after killing two black youths. Upon his release, Derek vows to change; he hopes to prevent his brother, Danny, who idolizes Derek, from following in his footsteps.

Title: 91. Once Upon a Time in the West
Short Description: A mysterious stranger with a harmonica joins forces with a notorious desperado to protect a beautiful widow from a ruthless assassin working for the railroad.

Title: 92. Grave of the Fireflies
Short Description: A young boy and his little sister struggle to survive in Japan during World War II.

Title: 93. Casablanca
Short Description: A cynical expatriate American cafe owner struggles to decide whether or not to help his former lover and her fugitive husband escape the Nazis in French Morocco.

Title: 94. The Intouchables
Short Description: After he becomes a quadriplegic from a paragliding accident, an aristocrat hires a young man from the projects to be his caregiver.

Title: 95. Psycho
Short Description: A secretary on the run for embezzlement takes refuge at a secluded California motel owned by a repressed man and his overbearing mother.

Title: 96. Cinema Paradiso
Short Description: Salvatore, a famous film director, returns to his hometown for the funeral of the local theater's film projectionist, Alfredo. He reminisces about his life as a young boy falling in love with cinema.

Title: 97. Rear Window
Short Description: A bored photographer recovering from a broken leg passes the time by watching his neighbors and begins to suspect one of them of murder.

Title: 98. Dear Zachary: A Letter to a Son About His Father
Short Description: A filmmaker decides to memorialize a murdered friend when his friend's ex-girlfriend announces she is expecting his son.

Title: 99. Modern Times
Short Description: The Tramp struggles to live in modern industrial society with the help of a young homeless woman.

Title: 100. City Lights
Short Description: With the aid of a wealthy erratic tippler, a dewy-eyed tramp who has fallen in love with a sightless flower girl accumulates money to be able to help her medically.

Title: 101. Senna
Short Description: A documentary on Brazilian Formula One racing driver Ayrton Senna, who won the F1 world championship three times before his death at age 34.

Title: 102. Sita Ramam
Short Description: An orphan soldier, Lieutenant Ram's life changes, after he gets a letter from a girl named Sita. He meets her and love blossoms between them. When he comes back to his camp in Kashmir,After he gets caught in jail, he sends a letter to Sita which won't reach her.

Title: 103. 20 Days in Mariupol
Short Description: As the Russian invasion begins, a team of Ukrainian journalists trapped in the besieged city of Mariupol struggle to continue their work documenting the war's atrocities.

Title: 104. The Best of Youth
Short Description: An Italian epic that follows the lives of two brothers from the 1960s to the 2000s.

Title: 105. Baraka
Short Description: A collection of expertly photographed scenes of human life and religion.

Title: 106. The Kashmir Files
Short Description: A heart-wrenching tale that captures the pain, suffering, and struggle of the Kashmiri Pandit community in 1990 and leads Krishna, a young college student, to set out on a quest to uncover the truth.

Title: 107. Kumbalangi Nights
Short Description: The film revolves around four brothers who share a love-hate relationship with each other. Their relationship progresses to another level when Saji, Boney, and Franky decide to help Bobby stand by his love.
Two high school sweethearts meet at a reunion after 22 years and reminisce about their past.

Title: 109. The Hole
Short Description: Distrust and uncertainty arise when four long-term inmates cautiously induct a new prisoner into their elaborate prison-break scheme.

Title: 110. Intoxicated by Love
Short Description: Story of Rumi, his friendship with Shams Tabrizi, the love he had for him and the great influence of Shams over him in his life, his poetry and his love for God.

Title: 111. For Sama
Short Description: FOR SAMA is both an intimate and epic journey into the female experience of war.

Title: 112. Gol Maal
Short Description: A man's simple lie to secure his job escalates into more complex lies when his orthodox boss gets suspicious.

Title: 113. Jersey
Short Description: A failed cricketer decides to revive his cricketing career in his late 30's despite everyone being skeptical of his ability to do so.

Title: 114. Sarpatta Parambarai
Short Description: When Sarpatta Parambarai is challenged to a do-or-die match, will Kabilan, a young labourer, put on the gloves himself and lead his clan to victory, or be dissuaded by his disapproving mother and dangerous politics?

Title: 115. Kaiva
Short Description: Inspired from the true incidents occurred in Bengaluru - 1983, Kaiva brings the visual grandeur of Old Bengaluru showing the lights of world famous Bengaluru Karaga and the dark underworld of the city as well.

Title: 116. Thalapathi
Short Description: An orphan named Surya raised in a slum befriends a good crime boss named Devaraj and works for him. Their existence is threatened when a new honest district collector arrives.

Title: 117. Home
Short Description: With aerial footage from fifty-four countries, 'Home' is a depiction of how Earth's problems are all interlinked.

Title: 118. The Girl with the Red Scarf
Short Description: Story of a dilemma between a woman's love and her logic. Asya, a young girl with a strict mother, meets Ilyas, who is a womanizer city man, and they quickly fall in love. They get over the hardships and have a happy marriage. However, after he helps a man one night, Ilyas' life changes forever and he leaves Asya and their son for another woman and doesn't come back.

Title: 119. The King of the Street Cleaners
Short Description: Going through his daily routine in a stereotypical neighborhood, a street cleaner falls in love with a charwoman. Unfortunately for him, so does his boss.

Title: 120. Zübük
Short Description: Zübük gets expelled from the political party that he is a member of, due to corruption. The journalist Yasar wants to make a news story about his case and investigates Zübük's doings. Yasar gets baffled at the sly tricks Zübük played on his village people.

Title: 121. Inglourious Basterds
Short Description: In Nazi-occupied France during World War II, a plan to assassinate Nazi leaders by a group of Jewish U.S. soldiers coincides with a theatre owner's vengeful plans for the same.

Title: 122. Avengers: Endgame
Short Description: After the devastating events of Avengers: Infinity War (2018), the universe is in ruins. With the help of remaining allies, the Avengers assemble once more in order to reverse Thanos' actions and restore balance to the universe.

Title: 123. Memento
Short Description: Leonard Shelby, an insurance investigator, suffers from anterograde amnesia and uses notes and tattoos to hunt for the man he thinks killed his wife, which is the last thing he remembers.

Title: 124. Apocalypse Now
Short Description: A U.S. Army officer serving in Vietnam is tasked with assassinating a renegade Special Forces Colonel who sees himself as a god.

Title: 125. Raiders of the Lost Ark
Short Description: In 1936, archaeologists and adventurers of the U.S. government hired Indiana Jones to find the Ark of the Covenant before the Nazis could obtain its extraordinary powers.

Title: 126. The Dark Knight Rises
Short Description: Bane, an imposing terrorist, attacks Gotham City and disrupts its eight-year-long period of peace. This forces Bruce Wayne to come out of hiding and don the cape and cowl of Batman again.

Title: 127. Aliens
Short Description: Decades after surviving the Nostromo incident, Ellen Ripley is sent out to re-establish contact with a terraforming colony but finds herself battling the Alien Queen and her offspring.

Title: 128. The Shining
Short Description: A family heads to an isolated hotel for the winter, where a sinister presence influences the father into violence. At the same time, his psychic son sees horrifying forebodings from both the past and the future.

Title: 129. Avengers: Infinity War
Short Description: The Avengers and their allies must be willing to sacrifice all in an attempt to defeat the powerful Thanos before his blitz of devastation and ruin puts an end to the universe.

Title: 130. Maharaja
Short Description: A barber seeks vengeance after his home is burglarized, cryptically telling police his "lakshmi" has been taken, leaving them uncertain if it's a person or object. His quest to recover the elusive "lakshmi" unfolds.

Title: 131. Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse
Short Description: Teen Miles Morales becomes the Spider-Man of his universe and must join with five spider-powered individuals from other dimensions to stop a threat for all realities.

Title: 132. Amadeus
Short Description: The life, success and troubles of Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, as told by Antonio Salieri, the contemporaneous composer who was deeply jealous of Mozart's talent and claimed to have murdered him.

Title: 133. Your Name.
Short Description: Two teenagers share a profound, magical connection upon discovering they are swapping bodies. Things manage to become even more complicated when the boy and girl decide to meet in person.

Title: 134. The Lives of Others
Short Description: In 1984 East Berlin, an agent of the secret police conducting surveillance on a writer and his lover finds himself becoming increasingly absorbed by their lives.

Title: 135. Coco
Short Description: Aspiring musician Miguel, confronted with his family's ancestral ban on music, enters the Land of the Dead to find his great-great-grandfather, a legendary singer.

Title: 136. WALL·E
Short Description: A robot who is responsible for cleaning a waste-covered Earth meets another robot and falls in love with her. Together, they set out on a journey that will alter the fate of mankind.

Title: 137. 3 Idiots
Short Description: Two friends are searching for their long lost companion. They revisit their college days and recall the memories of their friend who inspired them to think differently, even as the rest of the world called them "idiots".

Title: 138. Das Boot
Short Description: A German U-boat stalks the frigid waters of the North Atlantic as its young crew experience the sheer terror and claustrophobic life of a submariner in World War II.

Title: 139. Sunset Boulevard
Short Description: A screenwriter develops a dangerous relationship with a faded film star determined to make a triumphant return.

Title: 140. Capernaum
Short Description: While serving a five-year sentence for a violent crime, a 12-year-old boy sues his parents for neglect.

Title: 141. Witness for the Prosecution
Short Description: A veteran British barrister must defend his client in a murder trial that has surprise after surprise.

Title: 142. Lost Ladies
Short Description: The misadventures of two young brides who get lost from the same train. From mistaken identities to laugh-out-aloud escapades, the ensuing chaos guarantees laughter galore and heartwarming moments.

Title: 143. Paths of Glory
Short Description: A colonel defends three of his soldiers in a court-martial after they abandon a suicidal attack.

Title: 144. Meiyazhagan
Short Description: A man's life is changed when he bumps into someone from his hometown in this moving Tamil-language drama; gentle scenes are occasionally punctuated by sporting threat and recollections of violence.

Title: 145. High and Low
Short Description: An executive of a Yokohama shoe company becomes a victim of extortion when his chauffeur's son is kidnapped by mistake and held for ransom.

Title: 146. The Great Dictator
Short Description: Dictator Adenoid Hynkel tries to expand his empire while a poor Jewish barber tries to avoid persecution from Hynkel's regime.

Title: 147. Kaithi
Short Description: Dilli, an ex-convict, endeavours to meet his daughter for the first time after leaving prison. However, his attempts are interrupted due to a drug raid planned by Inspector Bejoy.

Title: 148. Samsara
Short Description: Filmed over nearly five years in twenty-five countries on five continents, and shot on seventy-millimetre film, Samsara transports us to the varied worlds of sacred grounds, disaster zones, industrial complexes, and natural wonders.

Title: 149. Woman in the Dunes
Short Description: An entomologist on vacation is trapped by local villagers into living with a woman whose life task is shoveling sand for them.

Title: 150. The Salt of the Earth
Short Description: The life and work of photographer Sebastião Salgado, who has spent forty years documenting societies in hidden corners of the world.

Title: 151. The Cove
Short Description: Using state-of-the-art equipment, a group of activists, led by renowned dolphin trainer Ric O'Barry, infiltrate a cove near Taijii, Japan to expose both a shocking instance of animal abuse and a serious threat to human health.

Title: 152. The Pinchcliffe Grand Prix
Short Description: Reodor Felgen decides that he will enter a car race to defeat his former friend who has stolen his plans for a car.

Title: 153. Asuran
Short Description: The teenage son of a farmer from an underprivileged caste kills a rich, upper caste landlord. How the pacifist farmer saves his hot-blooded son is the rest of the story.

Title: 154. Sansho the Bailiff

Short Description: Female radio reporter Marcia Jeffries turns folk-singing drifter Larry "Lonesome" Rhodes into a powerful media star who becomes utterly detestable during his meteoric rise.

Title: 319. They Shall Not Grow Old
Short Description: A documentary about World War I with never-before-seen footage to commemorate the centennial of the end of the war.

Title: 320. The Kid
Short Description: The Tramp cares for an abandoned child, but events put their relationship in jeopardy.

Title: 321. A Man Escaped
Short Description: A captured French Resistance fighter during World War II engineers a daunting escape from a German prison in France.

Title: 322. Uri: The Surgical Strike
Short Description: Indian army special forces execute a covert operation, avenging the killing of fellow army men at their base by a terrorist group.

Title: 323. Koyaanisqatsi
Short Description: A collection of expertly photographed phenomena with no conventional plot. The footage focuses on the relationship between nature, humanity, and technology.

Title: 324. Searching for Sugar Man
Short Description: Two South Africans set out to discover what happened to their unlikely musical hero, the mysterious 1970s rock n roller, Rodriguez.

Title: 325. Gangs of Wasseypur
Short Description: A clash between Sultan and Shahid Khan leads to the expulsion of Khan from Wasseypur, and ignites a deadly blood feud spanning three generations.

Title: 326. Dersu Uzala
Short Description: The Russian army sends an explorer on an expedition to the snowy Siberian wilderness where he makes friends with a seasoned local hunter.

Title: 327. Super Deluxe
Short Description: An unfaithful newly-wed wife, an estranged father, a priest and an angry son suddenly find themselves in the most unexpected predicaments, each poised to experience their destiny, all on one fateful day.

Title: 328. Close-Up
Short Description: The true story of Hossain Sabzian, a cinephile who impersonated the director Mohsen Makhmalbaf to convince a family they would star in his so-called new film.

Title: 329. My Father and My Son
Short Description: The family of a left-wing journalist is torn apart after the military coup of Turkey in 1980.

Title: 330. Lion of the Desert
Short Description: In 1929, Italian Fascist dictator Benito Mussolini appoints General Rodolfo Graziani as colonial governor to Italian Libya with orders to stamp-out all resistance from Libyan nationalists led by rebel guerrilla leader Omar Mukhtar.

Title: 331. Rangasthalam
Short Description: Chitti Babu begins to suspect his elder brother's life is in danger after they team up to lock horns with their village president and overthrow his unlawful 30 year old regime.

Title: 332. A Brighter Summer Day
Short Description: Based on a true story, primarily on a conflict between two youth gangs, a 14-year-old boy's girlfriend conflicts with the head of one gang for an unclear reason, until finally the conflict comes to a violent climax.

Title: 333. Paradise Lost: The Child Murders at Robin Hood Hills
Short Description: A horrific triple child murder leads to an indictment and trial of three nonconformist boys based on questionable evidence.

Title: 334. Ayla: The Daughter of War
Short Description: Sergeant Süleyman finds a little girl on a battlefield during the Korean War. He takes her and names her Ayla. Fifteen months later, Süleyman's brigade is told they will be returning to Turkey, and he is reluctant to leave her behind.

Title: 335. The Mountain II
Short Description: In a desolate war zone where screams of the innocent echo, seven Maroon Berets will dance with death on the very line between disaster and valor.

Title: 336. Paris Is Burning
Short Description: A chronicle of New York's drag scene in the 1980s, focusing on balls, voguing and the ambitions and dreams of those who gave the era its warmth and vitality.

Title: 337. Pather Panchali
Short Description: Impoverished priest Harihar Ray, dreaming of a better life for himself and his family, leaves his rural Bengal village in search of work.

Title: 338. Hera Pheri
Short Description: Two tenants and a landlord look for answers to all their money problems - but when their opportunity arrives, will they know what to do with it?

Title: 339. The Easy Life
Short Description: An impulsive braggart takes a shy law student with him for a two-day road trip from Rome to Tuscany.

Title: 340. Hi Nanna
Short Description: A single father begins to narrate the story of the missing mother to his child and nothing remains the same.

Title: 341. Hope
Short Description: Story of an 8-year-old girl who faces a horrible rape that damages her internally and affects her emotionally, trying to overcome all the obstacles following the incident with the good support of those around her.

Title: 342. Bhaag Milkha Bhaag
Short Description: The truth behind the ascension of Milkha Singh, who was scarred by of the India-Pakistan partition.

Title: 343. Swades
Short Description: A successful Indian scientist returns to an Indian village to take his nanny to America with him and in the process rediscovers his roots.

Title: 344. The Ascent
Short Description: Two Soviet partisans on a mission to gather food contend with the winter cold, the occupying Germans, and their own psyches.

Title: 345. Late Spring
Short Description: Several people try to talk 27-year-old Noriko into marrying, but all she wants is to keep on caring for her widowed father.

Title: 346. Khosla Ka Ghosla!
Short Description: A Delhi-based retired middle-class man tries half-heartedly to get his land back from a swindling property dealer with the help of his sons and their friends.

Title: 347. 13th
Short Description: An in-depth look at the prison system in the United States and how it reveals the nation's history of racial inequality.

Title: 348. I Am Cuba
Short Description: Four vignettes about the lives of the Cuban people set during the pre-revolutionary era.

Title: 349. Vikram Vedha
Short Description: Vikram, a no-nonsense police officer, accompanied by Simon, his partner, is on the hunt to capture Vedha, a smuggler and a murderer. Vedha tries to change Vikram's life, which leads to a conflict.

Title: 350. Ordet
Short Description: Follows the lives of the Borgen family, as they deal with inner conflict, as well as religious conflict with each other, and the rest of the town.

Title: 351. The Young and the Damned
Short Description: A group of juvenile delinquents live a violent and crime-filled life in the festering slums of Mexico City, as the morals of young Pedro are gradually corrupted and destroyed by the others.

Title: 352. Umberto D.
Short Description: An elderly man and his dog struggle to survive on his government pension in Rome.

Title: 353. Life and a Day
Short Description: Somaieh, the youngest daughter of an indigent family, is getting married and fear is overwhelming each and every member of the family regarding how to overcome their difficulties after she's gone.

Title: 354. Before the Flood
Short Description: A look at how climate change affects our environment and what society can do to prevent the demise of endangered species, ecosystems and native communities across the planet.

Title: 355. Dhuruvangal Pathinaaru
Short Description: A police officer retires after an accident during a case investigation. Years later, he is forced to relive the past as he narrates the story to his friend's son.

Title: 356. Ivan Vasilyevich Changes His Profession
Short Description: An ordinary Soviet building manager, living in the 20th century, looks like Tsar of All Rus' - Ivan IV the Terrible (1530 - 1584). He'd never known this, until his neighbor created a time machine.

Title: 357. Aparajito
Short Description: Following his father's death, a boy leaves home to study in Calcutta, while his mother must face a life alone.

Title: 358. Champion
Short Description: A true love and success story from the 1990s Turkey, revolving around a jockey (Halis Karatas), a horse (Bold Pilot) and the daughter of the horse's owner who is at the same time the voluntary caretaker of the horse.

Title: 359. Ballad of a Soldier
Short Description: Young Russian soldier Alyosha earns a medal, but asks to visit his mother instead. His journey recounts various kinds of love during wartime.

Title: 360. Office Romance
Short Description: The life of entire statistical bureau becomes crazy when an ordinary worker, a shy man, falls in love with a boss, a strict woman.

Title: 361. Paan Singh Tomar
Short Description: The story of Paan Singh Tomar, an Indian athlete and seven-time national steeplechase champion who becomes one of the most feared dacoits in Chambal Valley after his retirement.

Title: 362. The Shop on Main Street
Short Description: A carpenter in the Fascist Slovak State is appointed "Aryan controller" of a Jewish widow's store.

Title: 363. I Am a Fugitive from a Chain Gang
Short Description: A World War I veteran and aspiring engineer tries to re-enter civilian life. After being unwillingly caught up in a robbery, he suffers the intolerable conditions of a Southern chain gang, struggling to clear his name and prove his worth.

Title: 364. Maanaadu
Short Description: On the day of a public conference by the state's Chief Minister, his bodyguard and a police officer are stuck in a time loop.

Title: 365. Shahid
Short Description: The account of Human Rights lawyer Shahid Azmi, an ordinary citizen with an extraordinary commitment to justice.

Title: 366. Jigarthanda
Short Description: An aspiring director targets a ruthless gangster because he wants to make a violent gangster film. His discreet attempts to research the gangster fail miserably. Finally when he gets caught snooping, things hit the fan.

Title: 367. Pocket Hercules: Naim Süleymanoglu
Short Description: The biography of Turkish weightlifter and Olympic champion Naim Suleymanoglu.

Title: 368. Ustad Hotel
Short Description: Faisi wants to go to UK to become a professional chef but circumstances force him to assist his grandfather in a small restaurant in Kozhikode city, changing his outlook on life forever.

Title: 369. Theeran Adhigaram Ondru
Short Description: Theeran, a police officer, is entrusted with the task to solve the mystery behind a series of murders. The only clue left behind is that all the murders are committed in the same pattern.

Title: 370. Vaaranam Aayiram
Short Description: A father and son help each other through growing up, romance, tragedy, and adventure.

Title: 371. Athadu
Short Description: A gunman for hire is framed for murder, and assumes a dead man's identity while hiding from the police.

Title: 372. Ghilli
Short Description: Velu, an aspiring kabaddi player, goes to Madurai to participate in a regional match, where he rescues Dhanalakshmi from Muthupandi, a powerful man keen on marrying the girl against her will.

Title: 373. Bommarillu
Short Description: A young man realizes that he has to push back against his domineering father if he wants to find true happiness and love.

Title: 374. Mad Max: Fury Road
Short Description: In a post-apocalyptic wasteland, a woman rebels against a tyrannical ruler in search for her homeland with the aid of a group of female prisoners, a psychotic worshipper and a drifter named Max.

Title: 375. The Wizard of Oz
Short Description: Young Dorothy Gale and her dog Toto are swept away by a tornado from their Kansas farm to the magical Land of Oz and embark on a quest with three new friends to see the Wizard, who can return her to her home and fulfill the others' wishes.

Title: 376. Gone Girl
Short Description: The husband of a missing woman becomes the chief suspect in her disappearance.

Title: 377. Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2
Short Description: As the battle between the forces of good and evil in the wizarding world escalates, Harry Potter draws ever closer to his final confrontation with Voldemort.

Title: 378. Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl
Short Description: Blacksmith Will Turner teams up with eccentric pirate "Captain" Jack Sparrow to save Elizabeth Swann, the governor's daughter and his love, from Jack's former pirate allies, who are now undead.

Title: 379. The Handmaiden
Short Description: In 1930s Korea, a girl is hired as a handmaiden to a Japanese heiress who lives a secluded life on a countryside estate. But the maid has a secret: She is a pickpocket recruited by a swindler to help seduce the Lady and steal her fortune.

Title: 380. Blade Runner
Short Description: A blade runner must pursue and terminate four replicants who stole a ship in space and have returned to Earth to find their creator.

Title: 381. Hacksaw Ridge
Short Description: World War II American Army Medic Desmond T. Doss, serving during the Battle of Okinawa, refuses to kill people and becomes the first man in American history to receive the Medal of Honor without firing a shot.

Title: 382. Fargo
Short Description: Minnesota car salesman Jerry Lundegaard's inept crime falls apart due to his and his henchmen's bungling and the persistent police work of the quite pregnant Marge Gunderson.

Title: 383. Dead Poets Society
Short Description: Maverick teacher John Keating returns in 1959 to the prestigious New England boys' boarding school where he was once a star student, using poetry to embolden his pupils to new heights of self-expression.

Title: 384. Jaws
Short Description: When a massive killer shark unleashes chaos on a beach community off Long Island, it's up to a local sheriff, a marine biologist, and an old seafarer to hunt the beast down.

Title: 385. The Grand Budapest Hotel
Short Description: A writer encounters the owner of an aging high-class hotel, who tells him of his early years serving as a lobby boy in the hotel's glorious years under an exceptional concierge.

Title: 386. Catch Me If You Can
Short Description: Barely 17 yet, Frank is a skilled forger who has passed as a doctor, lawyer and pilot. FBI agent Carl becomes obsessed with tracking down the con man, who only revels in the pursuit.

Title: 387. Ratatouille
Short Description: A rat who can cook makes an unusual alliance with a young kitchen worker at a famous Paris restaurant.

Title: 388. Stand by Me
Short Description: A writer recounts a childhood journey with his friends to find the body of a missing boy.

Title: 389. The Sound of Music
Short Description: A young novice is sent by her convent in 1930s Austria to become a governess to the seven children of a widowed naval officer.

Title: 390. The Big Lebowski
Short Description: Jeff "The Dude" Lebowski, mistaken for a millionaire of the same name, seeks restitution for his ruined rug and enlists his bowling buddies to help get it.

Title: 391. The Help
Short Description: An aspiring author during the civil rights movement of the 1960s decides to write a book detailing the African American maids' point of view on the white families for which they work, and the hardships they go through on a daily basis.

Title: 392. Memories of Murder
Short Description: In a small Korean province in 1986, two detectives struggle with the case of multiple young women being found raped and murdered by an unknown culprit.

Title: 393. The Terminator
Short Description: A cyborg assassin from the future attempts to find and kill a young woman who is destined to give birth to a warrior that will lead a resistance to save humankind from extinction.

Title: 394. Inside Out
Short Description: After young Riley is uprooted from her Midwest life and moved to San Francisco, her emotions - Joy, Fear, Anger, Disgust and Sadness - conflict on how best to navigate a new city, house, and school.

Title: 395. Chinatown
Short Description: A private detective hired to expose an adulterer in 1930s Los Angeles finds himself caught up in a web of deceit, corruption, and murder.

Title: 396. Trainspotting
Short Description: Renton, deeply immersed in the Edinburgh drug scene, tries to clean up and get out despite the allure of drugs and the influence of friends.

Title: 397. Ford v Ferrari
Short Description: American car designer Carroll Shelby and driver Ken Miles battle corporate interference and the laws of physics to build a revolutionary race car for Ford in order to defeat Ferrari at the 24 Hours of Le Mans in 1966.

Title: 398. Paris, Texas
Short Description: Travis Henderson, an aimless drifter who has been missing for four years, wanders out of the desert and must reconnect with society, himself, his life, and his family.

Title: 399. Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri
Short Description: A mother personally challenges the local authorities to solve her daughter's murder when they fail to catch the culprit.

Title: 400. How to Train Your Dragon
Short Description: A hapless young Viking who aspires to hunt dragons becomes the unlikely friend of a young dragon himself, and learns there may be more to the creatures than he assumed.

Title: 401. Into the Wild
Short Description: After graduating from Emory University, top student and athlete Christopher McCandless abandons his possessions, gives his entire $24,000 savings account to charity and hitchhikes to Alaska to live in the wilderness.

Title: 402. Room
Short Description: A little boy is held captive in a room with his mother since his birth, so he has never known the world outside.

Title: 403. The Exorcist
Short Description: When a mysterious entity possesses a young girl, her mother seeks the help of two Catholic priests to save her life.

Title: 404. V for Vendetta
Short Description: In a future British dystopian society, a shadowy freedom fighter, known only by the alias of "V", plots to overthrow the tyrannical government - with the help of a young woman.

Title: 405. Rocky
Short Description: A small-time Philadelphia boxer gets a supremely rare chance to fight the world heavyweight champion in a bout in which he strives to go the distance for his self-respect.

Title: 406. Logan
Short Description: In a future where mutants are nearly extinct, an elderly and weary Logan leads a quiet life. But when Laura, a mutant child pursued by scientists, comes to him for help, he must get her to safety.

Title: 407. Platoon
Short Description: Chris Taylor, a neophyte recruit in Vietnam, finds himself caught in a battle of wills between two sergeants, one good and the other evil. A shrewd examination of the brutality of war and the duality of man in conflict.

Title: 408. The Deer Hunter
Short Description: An in-depth examination of the ways in which the Vietnam War impacts and disrupts the lives of several friends in a small steel mill town in Pennsylvania.

Title: 409. Monsters, Inc.
Short Description: In order to power the city, monsters have to scare children so that they scream. However, the children are toxic to the monsters, and after a child gets through, two monsters realize things may not be what they think.

Title: 410. Barry Lyndon
Short Description: An Irish rogue wins the heart of a rich widow and assumes her dead husband's aristocratic position in 18th-century England.

Title: 411. Warrior
Short Description: The youngest son of an alcoholic former boxer returns home, where he's trained by his father for competition in a mixed martial arts tournament - a path that puts the fighter on a collision course with his estranged, older brother.

Title: 412. Before Sunrise
Short Description: A young man and woman meet on a train in Europe, and wind up spending one evening together in Vienna. Unfortunately, both know that this will probably be their only night together.

Title: 413. Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels
Short Description: When four small-time criminals lose a rigged poker game against a London kingpin, he gives them one week to settle their enormous debt.

Title: 414. 12 Years a Slave
Short Description: In the antebellum United States, Solomon Northup, a free black man from upstate New York, is abducted and sold into slavery.

Title: 415. Spotlight
Short Description: The true story of how the Boston Globe uncovered the massive scandal of child molestation and cover-up within the local Catholic Archdiocese, shaking the entire Catholic Church to its core.

Title: 416. Portrait of a Lady on Fire
Short Description: On an isolated island in Brittany at the end of the eighteenth century, a female painter is obliged to paint a wedding portrait of a young woman.

Title: 417. In the Mood for Love
Short Description: Two neighbors form a strong bond after both suspect extramarital activities of their spouses. However, they agree to keep their bond platonic so as not to commit similar wrongs.

Title: 418. Gran Torino
Short Description: After a Hmong teenager tries to steal his prized 1972 Gran Torino, a disgruntled, prejudiced Korean War veteran seeks to redeem both the boy and himself.

Title: 419. La haine
Short Description: 24 hours in the lives of three young men in the French suburbs the day after a violent riot.

Title: 420. Rush
Short Description: James Hunt and Niki Lauda, two extremely skilled Formula One racers, have an intense rivalry with each other. However, it is their enmity that pushes them to their limits.

Title: 421. Million Dollar Baby
Short Description: Frankie, an ill-tempered old coach, reluctantly agrees to train aspiring boxer Maggie. Impressed with her determination and talent, he helps her become the best and the two soon form a close bond.

Title: 422. Ben-Hur
Short Description: A Jewish prince is betrayed and sent into slavery by a Roman friend in 1st-century Jerusalem, but it's not long before he regains his freedom and comes back for revenge.

Title: 423. A Silent Voice: The Movie
Short Description: A deaf girl, Shoko, is bullied by the popular Shoya. As Shoya continues to bully Shoko, the class turns its back on him. Shoko transfers and Shoya grows up as an outcast. Alone and depressed, the regretful Shoya finds Shoko to make amends.

Title: 424. My Neighbor Totoro
Short Description: When two girls move to the country to be near their ailing mother, they have adventures with the wondrous forest spirits who live nearby.

Title: 425. Hachi: A Dog's Tale
Short Description: Professor Wilson discovers a lost Akita puppy on his way home. Despite objections from his wife, Hachi endears himself to the family and grows to be Parker's loyal companion. As their bond grows deeper, a beautiful relationship unfolds.

Title: 426. The Seventh Seal
Short Description: A knight returning to Sweden after the Crusades seeks answers about life, death, and the existence of God as he plays chess against the Grim Reaper during the Black Plague.

Title: 427. Network
Short Description: A television network cynically exploits a deranged former anchor's ravings and revelations about mass media for its own profit, but finds that his message may be difficult to control.

Title: 428. The Iron Giant
Short Description: A young boy befriends a giant robot from outer space that a paranoid government agent wants to destroy.

Title: 429. Raging Bull
Short Description: The life of boxer Jake LaMotta, whose violence and temper that led him to the top in the ring destroyed his life outside of it.

Title: 430. Wild Tales
Short Description: Six short stories that explore the extremities of human behavior involving people in distress.

Title: 431. In the Name of the Father
Short Description: An Irish man's coerced confession to an I.R.A. bombing he did not commit results in the imprisonment of his father as well. Meanwhile, a British lawyer fights to clear their names and free them.

Title: 432. Before Sunset
Short Description: Nine years after Jesse and Celine first met, they encounter each other again on the French leg of Jesse's book tour.

Title: 433. Mary and Max
Short Description: In 1976 Melbourne, a lonely 8-year-old girl strikes up a correspondence with an unlikely pen pal: a severely obese 44-year-old New Yorker with Asperger's syndrome.

Title: 434. Rebecca
Short Description: A self-conscious woman juggles adjusting to her new role as an aristocrat's wife and avoiding being intimidated by his first wife's spectral presence.

Title: 435. The Red Shoes
Short Description: A young ballet dancer is torn between the man she loves and her pursuit to become a prima ballerina.

Title: 436. On the Waterfront
Short Description: An ex-prize fighter turned New Jersey longshoreman struggles to stand up to his corrupt union bosses, including his older brother, as he starts to connect with the grieving sister of one of the syndicate's victims.

Title: 437. The Bridge on the River Kwai
Short Description: British POWs are forced to build a railway bridge across the river Kwai for their Japanese captors in occupied Burma, not knowing that the allied forces are planning a daring commando raid through the jungle to destroy it.

Title: 438. PK
Short Description: An alien on Earth loses the only device he can use to communicate with his spaceship. His innocent nature and child-like questions force the country to evaluate the impact of religious views on people.

Title: 439. Hotel Rwanda
Short Description: Paul Rusesabagina, a hotel manager, houses over a thousand Tutsi refugees during their struggle against the Hutu militia in Rwanda, Africa.

Title: 440. The Third Man
Short Description: Pulp novelist Holly Martins travels to shadowy, postwar Vienna, only to find himself investigating the mysterious death of an old friend, Harry Lime.

Title: 441. Neon Genesis Evangelion: The End of Evangelion
Short Description: Concurrent theatrical ending of the TV series Neon Genesis Evangelion (1995).

Title: 442. Paper Moon
Short Description: During the Great Depression, a con man finds himself saddled with a young girl who may or may not be his daughter, and the two forge an unlikely partnership.

Title: 443. Bajrangi Bhaijaan
Short Description: An Indian man with a magnanimous heart takes a young mute Pakistani girl back to her homeland to reunite her with her family.

Title: 444. The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance
Short Description: A senator returns to a Western town for the funeral of an old friend and tells the story of his origins.

Title: 445. Fanny and Alexander
Short Description: Two young Swedish children in the 1900s experience the many comedies and tragedies of their lively and affectionate theatrical family, the Ekdahls.

Title: 446. It Happened One Night
Short Description: A rogue reporter trailing a runaway heiress for a big story joins her on a bus heading from Florida to New York and they end up stuck with each other when the bus leaves them behind at one of the stops along the way.

Title: 447. The Grapes of Wrath
Short Description: An Oklahoma family, driven off their farm by the poverty and hopelessness of the Dust Bowl, joins the westward migration to California, suffering the misfortunes of the homeless in the Great Depression.

Title: 448. The Best Years of Our Lives
Short Description: Three World War II veterans, two of them traumatized or disabled, return home to the American midwest to discover that they and their families have been irreparably changed.

Title: 449. All Quiet on the Western Front
Short Description: A German youth eagerly enters World War I, but his enthusiasm wanes as he gets a firsthand view of the horror.

Title: 450. Tokyo Story
Short Description: An old couple visit their children and grandchildren in the city, but receive little attention.

Title: 451. Wild Strawberries
Short Description: After living a life marked by coldness, an aging professor is forced to confront the emptiness of his existence.

Title: 452. What Is a Woman?
Short Description: Political commentator Matt Walsh explores the changing concepts of sex and gender in the digital age, particularly the transgender rights movement, anti-transgender bigotry, and what it means to be a woman.

Title: 453. Free Solo
Short Description: Alex Honnold faces the biggest challenge of his career, climbing El Capitan in Yosemite National Park. He pursues it Free Solo, which means climbing without a rope and alone.

Title: 454. Three Colors: Red
Short Description: A model discovers a retired judge is keen on invading people's privacy.

Title: 455. The Wages of Fear
Short Description: In a decrepit South American village, four men are hired to transport an urgent nitroglycerine shipment without the equipment that would make it safe.

Title: 456. The Battle of Algiers
Short Description: In the 1950s, fear and violence escalate as the people of Algiers fight for independence from the French government.

Title: 457. Yi Yi
Short Description: Each member of a middle-class Taipei family seeks to reconcile past and present relationships within their daily lives.

Title: 458. To Be or Not to Be
Short Description: During the German occupation of Poland, an acting troupe becomes embroiled in a Polish soldier's efforts to track down a German spy.

Title: 459. Mr. Smith Goes to Washington
Short Description: A naive youth leader is appointed to fill a vacancy in the U.S. Senate. His idealistic plans promptly collide with corruption at home and subterfuge from his hero in Washington, but he tries to forge ahead despite attacks on his character.

Title: 460. I Want to Eat Your Pancreas
Short Description: A high school student discovers one of his classmates, Sakura Yamauchi, is suffering from a terminal illness. This secret brings the two together, as she lives out her final moments.

Title: 461. My Octopus Teacher
Short Description: A filmmaker forges an unusual friendship with an octopus living in a South African kelp forest, learning as the animal shares the mysteries of her world.

Title: 462. Sunrise
Short Description: A sophisticated city woman seduces a farmer and convinces him to murder his wife and join her in the city, but he ends up rekindling his romance with his wife when he changes his mind at the last moment.

Title: 463. The Message
Short Description: Historical fresco recounting the life and times of the Prophet Mohammed, the last of the Abrahamic religion, in the sense that, according to Islam, he completed and sealed the monotheistic revelation made to Abraham.

Title: 464. The Last Waltz
Short Description: A film account and presentation of the final concert of The Band.

Title: 465. Nights of Cabiria
Short Description: A waifish prostitute wanders the streets of Rome looking for true love but finds only heartbreak.

Title: 466. The General
Short Description: After being rejected by the Confederate military, not realizing it was due to his crucial civilian role, an engineer must single-handedly recapture his beloved locomotive after it is seized by Union spies and return it through enemy lines.

Title: 467. The Passion of Joan of Arc
Short Description: In 1431, Jeanne d'Arc is placed on trial on charges of heresy. The ecclesiastical jurists attempt to force Jeanne to recant her claims of holy visions.

Title: 468. The Miracle Worker
Short Description: The story of Anne Sullivan's struggle to teach the blind, deaf and mute child Helen Keller how to understand and communicate.

Title: 469. Blackfish
Short Description: A documentary following the controversial captivity of killer whales, and its dangers for both humans and whales.

Title: 470. A Moment to Remember
Short Description: A young couple's enduring love is tested when 27-year-old Su-jin is diagnosed with a rare form of Alzheimer's disease.

Title: 471. Wolf Children
Short Description: After her werewolf lover unexpectedly dies in an accident while hunting for food for their children, a young woman must find ways to raise the werewolf son and daughter that she had with him while keeping their trait hidden from society.

Title: 472. Farewell My Concubine
Short Description: Two boys meet at an opera training school in Peking in 1924. Their resulting friendship will span nearly 70 years and endure some of the most troublesome times in China's history.

Title: 473. Jean de Florette
Short Description: A greedy landowner and his backward nephew conspire to block the only water source for an adjoining property in order to bankrupt the owner and force him to sell.

Title: 474. Z
Short Description: The public murder of a prominent politician and doctor amid a violent demonstration is covered up by military and government officials. A tenacious magistrate is determined not to let them get away with it.

Title: 475. Diabolique
Short Description: The wife and mistress of a loathed school principal plan to murder him with what they believe is the perfect alibi.

Title: 476. Inherit the Wind
Short Description: Based on a real-life case in 1925; two great lawyers argue the case for, and against, a Tennessee science teacher accused of the crime of teaching Darwin's theory of evolution.

Title: 477. Barfi!
Short Description: Three young people learn that love can neither be defined nor contained by society's definition of normal and abnormal.

Title: 478. A Christmas Carol
Short Description: Ebenezer Scrooge, a curmudgeonly, miserly businessman, has no time for sentimentality and largely views Christmas as a waste of time. However, this Christmas Eve, he will be visited by three spirits who will show him the error of his ways.

Title: 479. The First Slam Dunk
Short Description: Follows 17-year-old Ryota Miyagi, who struggles to accomplish his late elder brother's dream of becoming a basketball star.

Title: 480. Autumn Sonata
Short Description: A devoted wife is visited by her mother, a successful concert pianist who had little time for her when she was young.

Title: 481. The Twilight Samurai
Short Description: As the feudal Japan era draws to a close, a widower samurai experiences difficulty balancing clan loyalties, 2 young daughters, an aged mother, and the sudden reappearance of his childhood sweetheart.

Title: 482. Army of Shadows
Short Description: An account of underground resistance fighters in Nazi-occupied France.

Title: 483. Where Is the Friend's House?
Short Description: Eight-year-old Ahmed has mistakenly taken his friend Mohammad's notebook. He wants to return it, or else his friend will be expelled from school. The boy determinedly sets out to find Mohammad's home in the neighbouring village.

Title: 484. Ugetsu
Short Description: A tale of ambition, family, love, and war set in the midst of the Japanese Civil Wars of the sixteenth century.

Title: 485. Udaan
Short Description: Expelled from his school, a 16-year old boy returns home to his abusive and oppressive father.

Title: 486. Lagaan: Once Upon a Time in India
Short Description: The people of a small village in Victorian India stake their future on a game of cricket against their ruthless British rulers.

Title: 487. Raise the Red Lantern
Short Description: China in the 1920s. After her father's death, Songlian is forced to marry the wealthy Master Chen. With three wives already, each living in a separate house, there is fierce competition for his attention and the privileges that are gained.

Title: 488. Faust
Short Description: The demon Mephisto wagers with God that he can corrupt a mortal man's soul.

Title: 489. The Gold Rush
Short Description: A prospector goes to the Klondike during the 1890s gold rush in hopes of making his fortune, and is smitten with a girl he sees in a dance hall.

Title: 490. Chak De! India
Short Description: Kabir Khan, the coach of the Indian Women's National Hockey Team, dreams of making his all-girls team emerge victorious against all odds.

Title: 491. Ace in the Hole
Short Description: Frustrated former journalist Chuck Tatum now working for an Albuquerque newspaper exploits a story about trading post owner Leo Minosa trapped in a cave to rekindle Chuck's career, but the story soon escalates into a media circus.

Title: 492. Masaan
Short Description: Along India's Ganges River, four people face prejudice, a strict moral code and a punishing caste system as they confront personal tragedies.

Title: 493. Queen
Short Description: A Delhi girl from a traditional family sets out on a solo honeymoon after her marriage gets cancelled.

Title: 494. Time of the Gypsies
Short Description: In this luminous tale set in the area around Sarajevo and in Italy, Perhan, an engaging young Romany (gypsy) with telekinetic powers, is seduced by the quick-cash world of petty crime, which threatens to destroy him and those he loves.

Title: 495. Rang De Basanti
Short Description: The story of six young Indians who assist an English woman to film a documentary on the freedom fighters from their past, and the events that lead them to relive the long-forgotten saga of freedom.

Title: 496. White Heat

Title: 497. Still: A Michael J. Fox Movie
Short Description: Follows the life of beloved actor and advocate Michael J. Fox, exploring his personal and professional triumphs and travails, and what happens when an incurable optimist confronts an incurable disease.

Title: 498. A Wednesday
Short Description: A retiring police officer reminisces about the most astounding day of his career. About a case that was never filed but continues to haunt him in his memories - the case of a man and a Wednesday.

Title: 499. A Short Film About Love
Short Description: A naive inexperienced young man spies on a woman who lives across the courtyard, and falls in love with her. He starts using tricks which he hopes will lead to them meeting.

Title: 500. Apollo 11
Short Description: A look at the Apollo 11 mission to land on the moon led by commander Neil Armstrong and pilots Buzz Aldrin and Mike Collins.

Title: 501. The Heiress
Short Description: A naive young woman falls for a handsome young man her emotionally abusive father suspects is only a fortune hunter.

Title: 502. Miracle in Cell No. 7
Short Description: A story about the love between a mentally-ill father and his lovingly adorable daughter.

Title: 503. Guilty
Short Description: An experienced investigator confronts several conflicting theories about the perpetrators of a violent double homicide.

Title: 504. The Grand Illusion

Title: 505. Sholay
Short Description: After his family is murdered by a notorious and ruthless bandit, a former police officer enlists the services of two outlaws to capture the bandit.

Title: 506. Tangerines

Title: 507. A Special Day

Title: 508. Montevideo: Taste of a Dream
Short Description: A story about the Serbian football team that decided to follow a dream that takes them on a journey to the first football World Cup in Montevideo, Uruguay in 1930. A dream that allows them to become true stars and living legends.

Title: 509. Rififi
Short Description: Four men plan a technically perfect crime, but the human element intervenes...

Title: 510. Woodstock
Short Description: Oscar-winning musical chronicle that brilliantly captures the three-day rock concert and celebration of peace and love that became a capstone for the Sixties.

Title: 511. Innocence
Short Description: Yusuf is released from prison after serving a ten-year sentence. He is scared of life outside as he goes to an address given to him by another prisoner.

Title: 512. The Dawn Wall
Short Description: In an unbelievable story of perseverance, free climber Tommy Caldwell and climbing partner Kevin Jorgeson attempt to scale the impossible 3000ft Dawn Wall of El Capitan.

Title: 513. Munna Bhai M.B.B.S.
Short Description: A gangster sets out to fulfill his father's dream of becoming a doctor.

Title: 514. Hearts of Darkness: A Filmmaker's Apocalypse

Title: 515. The Bandit
Short Description: Baran the Bandit, released from prison after 35 years, searches for vengeance and his lover.

Title: 516. Safety Last!
Short Description: A boy leaves his small country town and heads to the big city to get a job. As soon as he makes it big his sweetheart will join him and marry him. His enthusiasm to get ahead leads to some interesting adventures.

Title: 517. The Circus
Short Description: The Tramp finds work and the girl of his dreams at a circus.

Title: 518. Hridayam
Short Description: The emotional journey of Arun, his carefree bachelor days in engineering college, and how he matures through various phases of life.

Title: 520. The Color of Paradise

Title: 521. Section 375

Title: 522. OMG: Oh My God!

Title: 523. Charlie
Short Description: A young, nonconforming woman named Tessa gets entangled in a cat-and-mouse chase in the by-lanes of Kerala, hunting for a mysterious artist who previously lived in her apartment.

Title: 524. Major

Title: 525. George Harrison: Living in the Material World
Short Description: Filmmaker Martin Scorsese examines the life of musician George Harrison, weaving together interviews, concert footage, home movies and photographs.

Title: 526. Seaspiracy

Title: 527. Collective

Title: 528. Sarfarosh

Title: 529. Jo Jeeta Wohi Sikandar

Title: 530. Article 15

Title: 531. Black

Title: 532. RangiTaranga
Short Description: Mysterious events begin to unfold after a reclusive novelist and his wife move back to her ancestral village, followed by a journalist.

Title: 533. Kahaani

Title: 535. Cowspiracy: The Sustainability Secret
Short Description: Follow the shocking, yet humorous, journey of an aspiring environmentalist, as he daringly seeks to find the real solution to the most pressing environmental issues and true path to sustainability.

Title: 536. Indian

Title: 537. Early Summer
Short Description: A family chooses a match for their daughter Noriko, but she, surprisingly, has her own plans.

Title: 538. Thuppakki
Short Description: An army captain is on a mission to track down and destroy a terrorist gang and deactivate the sleeper cells under its command.

Title: 539. Pardon
Short Description: Based on a true event, the film tells the tragicomic story of three friends who end up in prison when they are mistaken as members of a terrorist organization.

Title: 540. Anand
Short Description: The story of a terminally ill man who wishes to live life to the fullest before the inevitable occurs, as told by his best friend.

Title: 541. Everything's Gonna Be Great

Title: 546. Kaththi
Short Description: A case of mistaken identity embroils an escaped convict in a fight against a large corporation intent on seizing a village's land.

Title: 547. Virunga
Short Description: A team of brave individuals risk their lives to protect the last mountain gorillas.

Title: 548. Roja
Short Description: A woman from a village in Tamil Nadu marries a sophisticated city dweller and moves with him to Kashmir, where all is rosy - until he gets kidnapped by militants.

Title: 549. Iqbal

Title: 550. Bombay
Short Description: A Hindu man and a Muslim woman fall in love in a small village and move to Mumbai, where they have two children. However, growing religious tensions and erupting riots threaten to tear the family apart.

Title: 551. Zeitgeist: Moving Forward

Title: 552. The Legend of Bhagat Singh
Short Description: The story of a young revolutionary who raised an armed resistance against the British rule in India.

Title: 553. Endless Corridor
