Title: 2885. Instant Family
Short Description: A couple find themselves in over their heads when they foster three children.

Title: 2886. Rango
Short Description: Rango is an ordinary chameleon who accidentally winds up in the town of Dirt, a lawless outpost in the Wild West in desperate need of a new sheriff.

Title: 2887. Rounders
Short Description: A young, reformed gambler must return to playing high stakes poker to help a friend pay off loan sharks, while balancing his relationship with his girlfriend and his commitments to law school.

Title: 2888. Say Anything
Short Description: A noble underachiever and a beautiful valedictorian fall in love the summer before she goes off to college.

Title: 2889. Death at a Funeral
Short Description: Chaos ensues when a man tries to expose a dark secret regarding a recently deceased patriarch of a dysfunctional British family.

Title: 2890. Jane Eyre
Short Description: A mousy governess who softens the heart of her employer soon discovers that he's hiding a terrible secret.

Title: 2891. Raising Arizona
Short Description: When a childless couple--an ex-con and an ex-cop--decide to help themselves to one of another family's quintuplets, their lives become more complicated than they anticipated.

Title: 2892. Lethal Weapon 2
Short Description: Riggs and Murtaugh are on the trail of South African diplomats who are using their immunity to engage in criminal activities.

Title: 2893. Snowden
Short Description: The NSA's illegal surveillance techniques are leaked to the public by one of the agency's employees, Edward Snowden, in the form of thousands of classified documents distributed to the press.

Title: 2894. Pusher
Short Description: A drug pusher grows increasingly desperate after a botched deal leaves him with a large debt to a ruthless drug lord.

Title: 2895. The Descendants
Short Description: A land baron tries to reconnect with his two daughters after his wife is seriously injured in a boating accident.

Title: 2896. We Are the Nobles
Short Description: Three spoiled children are cut off from their family fortune and forced to do the unthinkable: get jobs.

Title: 2897. The Way
Short Description: A father heads overseas to recover the body of his estranged son who died while traveling the "El camino de Santiago," and decides to take the pilgrimage himself.

Title: 2898. Alice in Wonderland
Short Description: Alice stumbles into the world of Wonderland. Will she get home? Not if the Queen of Hearts has her way.

Title: 2899. Enemy of the State
Short Description: A lawyer becomes targeted by a corrupt politician and his N.S.A. goons when he accidentally receives key evidence to a politically motivated crime.

Title: 2900. The Disaster Artist
Short Description: When aspiring actor Greg Sestero meets the weird and mysterious Tommy Wiseau in an acting class, they form a unique friendship and travel to Hollywood to make their dreams come true.

Title: 2901. Cinderella
Short Description: When Cinderella's cruel stepmother prevents her from attending the Royal Ball, she gets some unexpected help from the lovable mice Gus and Jaq and from her Fairy Godmother.

Title: 2902. One Hundred and One Dalmatians
Short Description: When a litter of Dalmatian puppies are abducted by the minions of Cruella De Vil, the owners must find them before she uses them for a diabolical fashion statement.

Title: 2903. Precious
Short Description: In New York City's Harlem circa 1987, an overweight, abused, illiterate teen who is pregnant with her second child is invited to enroll in an alternative school in hopes that she can re-route her life in a better direction.

Title: 2904. Matchstick Men
Short Description: A phobic con artist and his protégé are on the verge of pulling off a lucrative swindle when the former's teenage daughter arrives unexpectedly.

Title: 2905. Okja
Short Description: A young girl risks everything to prevent a powerful, multinational company from kidnapping her best friend - a fascinating beast named Okja.

Title: 2906. The Banker
Short Description: In the 1960s, two African-American entrepreneurs hire a working-class white man to pretend to be the head of their business empire while they pose as a janitor and chauffeur.

Title: 2907. Peter Pan
Short Description: Wendy and her brothers are whisked away to the magical world of Neverland with the hero of their stories, Peter Pan.

Title: 2908. To Live and Die in L.A.
Short Description: A fearless Secret Service agent will stop at nothing to bring down the counterfeiter who killed his partner.

Title: 2909. Across the Universe
Short Description: The music of The Beatles, New York in the 1960s, and the American youth's actions to protest the Vietnam War, form the backdrop for the romance between an upper-class American girl and a poor Liverpudlian artist.

Title: 2910. Fallen Leaves
Short Description: In modern-day Helsinki, two lonely souls in search of love meet by chance in a karaoke bar. However, their path to happiness is beset by obstacles - from lost phone numbers to mistaken addresses, alcoholism, and a charming stray dog.

Title: 2911. The Way Back
Short Description: Siberian gulag escapees travel four thousand miles by foot to freedom in India.

Title: 2912. The Hand of God
Short Description: In 1980s Naples, young Fabietto pursues his love for football as family tragedy strikes, shaping his uncertain but promising future as a filmmaker.

Title: 2913. The Ultimate Gift
Short Description: A deceased billionaire leaves his spoiled adult grandson a series of odd tasks to perform in order to receive "the ultimate gift," with the resentful grandson having no idea what that might be.

Title: 2914. The Squid and the Whale
Short Description: Follows two young boys dealing with their parents' divorce in Brooklyn in the 1980s.

Title: 2915. This Boy's Life
Short Description: The story about the relationship between a rebellious 1950s teenager and his abusive stepfather, based on the memoirs of writer and literature Professor Tobias Wolff.

Title: 2916. Good Morning, Vietnam
Short Description: In 1965, an unorthodox and irreverent DJ named Adrian Cronauer begins to shake up things when he is assigned to the U.S. Armed Services radio station in Vietnam.

Title: 2919. Four Lions
Short Description: Four incompetent British terrorists set out to train for and commit an act of terror.

Title: 2920. The Simpsons Movie
Short Description: After Homer pollutes the town's water supply, Springfield is encased in a gigantic dome by the EPA and the Simpsons are declared fugitives.

Title: 2921. Old Henry
Short Description: A farmer takes in an injured man with a satchel of cash. When a posse comes for the money, he must decide who to trust. Defending a siege, he reveals a gunslinging talent calling his true identity into question.

Title: 2922. The 12th Man

Title: 2923. Frida
Short Description: A biography of artist Frida Kahlo, who channeled the pain of a crippling injury and her tempestuous marriage into her work.

Title: 2924. Woman in Gold
Short Description: Maria Altmann, an octogenarian Jewish refugee, takes on the Austrian government to recover artwork she believes rightfully belongs to her family.

Title: 2925. Eddie the Eagle
Short Description: The story of Eddie Edwards, the notoriously tenacious British underdog ski jumper who charmed the world at the 1988 Winter Olympics.

Title: 2926. I Origins
Short Description: A molecular biologist and his laboratory partner uncover evidence that may fundamentally change society as we know it.

Title: 2927. La Femme Nikita
Short Description: Convicted felon Nikita isn't going to jail; she's given a new identity and trained, stylishly, as a top secret spy/assassin.

Title: 2928. Fish Tank
Short Description: Everything changes for 15-year-old Mia when her mum brings home a new boyfriend.

Title: 2929. Max Manus: Man of War
Short Description: The true story about one of the most brilliant saboteurs during World War II and his battle to overcome his inner demons.

Title: 2930. Take Shelter
Short Description: Plagued by a series of apocalyptic visions, a young husband and father questions whether to shelter his family from a coming storm, or from himself.

Title: 2931. Ghost World
Short Description: Two eccentric best friends graduate high school and respond to a man's romance-seeking newspaper ad as a gag, only to find their lives becoming increasingly complicated.

Title: 2932. Rocky II
Short Description: Rocky struggles in family life after his bout with Apollo Creed, while the embarrassed champ insistently goads him to accept a challenge for a rematch.

Title: 2933. Grosse Pointe Blank
Short Description: Professional assassin Martin Blank is sent on a mission to a small Detroit suburb, Grosse Pointe--where, by coincidence, his 10-year high-school reunion party is about to take place.

Title: 2934. Lady and the Tramp
Short Description: The romantic tale of a sheltered uptown Cocker Spaniel dog and a streetwise downtown Mutt.

Title: 2935. Blue Jasmine

Title: 2936. Local Hero

Title: 2937. I Can Only Imagine
Short Description: The inspiring and unknown true story behind MercyMe's beloved, chart topping song that brings ultimate hope to so many is a gripping reminder of the power of true forgiveness.

Title: 2938. Jason and the Argonauts
Short Description: The legendary Greek hero leads a team of intrepid adventurers in a perilous quest for the legendary Golden Fleece.

Title: 2939. The Gods Must Be Crazy
Short Description: A comic allegory about a traveling Bushman who encounters modern civilization and its stranger aspects, including a clumsy scientist and a band of revolutionaries.

Title: 2940. Mr. Holland's Opus
Short Description: A frustrated composer finds fulfillment as a high school music teacher.

Title: 2941. Paterson
Short Description: A quiet observation of the triumphs and defeats of daily life, along with the poetry evident in its smallest details.

Title: 2942. Betty Blue
Short Description: A lackadaisical handyman and aspiring novelist tries to support his younger girlfriend as she slowly succumbs to madness.

Title: 2943. Belle
Short Description: The biracial daughter, Dido Elizabeth Belle (Gugu Mbatha-Raw), of Royal Navy Captain Sir John Lindsay (Matthew Goode) is raised by aristocratic Great-uncle Lord William Murray, 1st Earl of Mansfield (Tom Wilkinson) in 18th century England.

Title: 2944. The Ice Storm
Short Description: In 1973 suburbia, several middle-class families experimenting with substance abuse and the swinging lifestyle find their lives spinning beyond their control.

Title: 2945. Submarine

Title: 2946. Eight Below

Title: 2947. The Boat That Rocked

Title: 2948. Nobody's Fool
Short Description: A stubborn man past his prime reflects on his life of strict independence and seeks more from himself.

Title: 2949. Assault on Precinct 13

Title: 2950. Pi

Title: 2951. Phantom of the Paradise

Title: 2952. House
Short Description: A schoolgirl and six of her classmates travel to her aunt's country home, which turns out to be haunted.

Title: 2953. Rescue Dawn
Short Description: A U.S. fighter pilot's epic struggle of survival after being shot down on a mission over Laos during the Vietnam War.

Title: 2954. Holy Spider
Short Description: A journalist descends into the dark underbelly of the Iranian holy city of Mashhad as she investigates the serial killings of sex workers by the so called "Spider Killer", who believes he is cleansing the streets of sinners.

Title: 2955. Invictus
Short Description: Nelson Mandela, in his first term as President of South Africa, initiates a unique venture to unite the Apartheid-torn land: enlist the national rugby team on a mission to win the 1995 Rugby World Cup.

Title: 2956. Star Trek IV: The Voyage Home
Short Description: To save Earth from an alien probe, Admiral James T. Kirk and his fugitive crew go back in time to San Francisco in 1986 to retrieve the only beings who can communicate with it: humpback whales.

Title: 2957. The Fundamentals of Caring
Short Description: A man suffering a family loss enrolls in a class about care-giving that changes his perspective on life.

Title: 2958. Antwone Fisher
Short Description: Antwone Fisher, a young navy man, is forced to see a psychiatrist after a violent outburst against a fellow crewman. During the course of treatment a painful past is revealed and a new hope begins.

Title: 2959. The Last Unicorn
Short Description: A beautiful unicorn sets out to learn if she truly is the last of her kind in this sparkling animated musical.

Title: 2960. The Bad News Bears
Short Description: An aging, down-on-his-luck ex-minor leaguer coaches a team of misfits in an ultra-competitive California little league.

Title: 2961. Cha Cha Real Smooth
Short Description: A young man who works as a Bar Mitzvah party host strikes up a friendship with a mother and her autistic daughter.

Title: 2962. Shaolin Soccer
Short Description: A young Shaolin follower reunites with his discouraged brothers to form a soccer team using their martial art skills to their advantage.

Title: 2963. I Stand Alone
Short Description: A horse butcher's life and mind begin to break down as he lashes out against various factions of society while attempting to reconnect with his estranged daughter.

Title: 2964. The Getaway
Short Description: A recently-released ex-con and his loyal wife go on the run after a heist goes awry.

Title: 2965. Moby Dick
Short Description: The sole survivor of a lost whaling ship relates the tale of his captain's self-destructive obsession to hunt the white whale, Moby Dick.

Title: 2966. The Negotiator
Short Description: In a desperate attempt to prove his innocence, a skilled police negotiator accused of corruption and murder takes hostages in a government office to gain the time he needs to find the truth.

Title: 2967. A Million Miles Away
Short Description: A biopic about Jose Hernandez and his path from a farm worker to becoming an engineer and an astronaut. A tale of perseverance, community and sacrifice to accomplish a seemingly impossible dream.

Title: 2968. Driving Miss Daisy
Short Description: An old Jewish woman and her African-American chauffeur in the American South have a relationship that grows and improves over the years.

Title: 2969. The Proposition
Short Description: A lawman apprehends a notorious outlaw and gives him nine days to kill his older brother, or else they'll execute his younger brother.

Title: 2970. Ten Inch Hero
Short Description: An artist gets a job at a beachside sandwich shop, where she hangs out with a techie, a flirt, a rocker, a hippie, and a Wiccan.

Title: 2971. Finding Forrester
Short Description: Forrester, the author of a famous book, decides to help Jamal, a 16-year-old student, discover his writing prowess by mentoring him and enrolling him into a prestigious private school.

Title: 2972. Big Night
Short Description: New Jersey, 1950s. Two brothers run an Italian restaurant. Business is not going well as a rival Italian restaurant is out-competing them. In a final effort to save the restaurant, the brothers plan to put on an evening of incredible food.

Title: 2973. Quest for Fire
Short Description: This story takes place in prehistoric time when three tribesmen search for a new fire source.

Title: 2974. Clerks II
Short Description: A calamity at Dante and Randal's shops sends them looking for new horizons - but they ultimately settle at the fast food empire Mooby's.

Title: 2975. Starred Up
Short Description: Eric Love, 19, is locked up in prison. On his first day, he assaults another inmate and several guards. He's offered group therapy and his dad, an inmate as well, tries to talk sense into him. Can he be rehabilitated?

Title: 2976. Entergalactic
Short Description: Jabari, a charming, streetwear-clad artist on the cusp of real success. After a chance run-in with his cool new photographer neighbor, Meadow, Jabari has to figure out whether he can make space for love in his life.

Title: 2977. Bambi
Short Description: The story of a young deer growing up in the forest.

Title: 2978. The Guard
Short Description: An unorthodox Irish policeman with a confrontational personality is partnered with an uptight F.B.I. agent to investigate an international drug-smuggling ring.

Title: 2979. What's Love Got to Do with It
Short Description: The story of singer Tina Turner's rise to stardom and how she gained the courage to break free from her abusive husband, Ike Turner.

Title: 2980. Thirteen Days
Short Description: In October 1962, the Kennedy administration struggles to contain the Cuban Missile Crisis.

Title: 2981. Eye in the Sky
Short Description: Col. Katherine Powell, a military officer in command of an operation to capture terrorists in Kenya, sees her mission escalate when a girl enters the kill zone, triggering an international dispute over the implications of modern warfare.

Title: 2982. Stand and Deliver
Short Description: The story of Jaime Escalante, a high school teacher who successfully inspired his dropout-prone students to learn calculus.

Title: 2983. Coming Home
Short Description: In 1968 California, a woman whose husband is a Marine officer fighting in Vietnam falls in love with a former high school classmate who suffered a paralyzing combat injury in the war.

Title: 2984. Seabiscuit
Short Description: True story of the undersized Depression-era racehorse whose victories lifted not only the spirits of the team behind it but also those of their nation.

Title: 2985. The Walk
Short Description: In 1974, high-wire artist Philippe Petit recruits a team of people to help him realize his dream: to walk the immense void between the World Trade Center towers.

Title: 2986. The Hundred-Foot Journey
Short Description: The Kadam family leaves India for France where they open a restaurant directly across the road from Madame Mallory's Michelin-starred eatery.

Title: 2987. Hustle & Flow
Short Description: With help from his friends, a Memphis pimp in a mid-life crisis attempts to become a successful hip-hop emcee.

Title: 2988. A Street Cat Named Bob
Short Description: The true feel-good story of how James Bowen, a busker and recovering drug addict, has his life transformed when he meets a stray ginger cat. Based on the international best selling book.

Title: 2989. North Country
Short Description: A fictionalized account of the first major successful sexual harassment case in the United States, Jenson vs. Eveleth Mines, where a woman who endured a range of abuse while working as a miner filed and won the landmark 1984 lawsuit.

Title: 2990. My Name Is Nobody
Short Description: A young, easy-going gunman worships and competes with a famed gunfighter, insisting that he must face down a gang of 150 outlaws before he can retire.

Title: 2991. Our Friend
Short Description: After receiving life-altering news, a couple finds unexpected support from their best friend, who puts his own life on hold and moves into their family home, bringing an impact much greater and more profound than anyone could have imagined.

Title: 2992. Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani
Short Description: Kabir and Naina bond during a trekking trip. Before Naina can express herself, Kabir leaves India to pursue his career. They meet again years later, but he still cherishes his dreams more than bonds.

Title: 2993. Murder in the First
Short Description: An eager and idealistic young attorney defends an Alcatraz prisoner accused of murdering a fellow inmate. The extenuating circumstances: his client had just spent over three years in solitary confinement.

Title: 2994. A Passage to India
Short Description: Cultural mistrust and false accusations doom a friendship in British colonial India between an Indian doctor, an Englishwoman engaged to marry a city magistrate, and an English educator.

Title: 2995. Far from Heaven
Short Description: In 1950s Connecticut, a flustered housewife faces a marital crisis and mounting racial tensions in the outside world.

Title: 2996. Waking Ned Devine
Short Description: When a lottery winner dies of shock, his fellow townsfolk attempt to claim the money.

Title: 2997. The Apartment
Short Description: A recently engaged man sees a former lover and becomes obsessed with meeting her again.

Title: 2998. Detroit
Short Description: Fact-based drama set during the 1967 Detroit riots in which a group of rogue police officers respond to a complaint with retribution rather than justice on their minds.

Title: 2999. Run Silent Run Deep
Short Description: A U.S. submarine commander, obsessed with sinking a particular Japanese ship, butts heads with his first officer and crew.

Title: 3000. The People vs. Larry Flynt
Short Description: The story of controversial pornography publisher Larry Flynt, and how he became a defender of free speech.

Title: 3001. The Captain
Short Description: In the last moments of World War II, a young German soldier fighting for survival finds a Nazi captain's uniform. Impersonating an officer, the man quickly takes on the monstrous identity of the perpetrators he's escaping from.

Title: 3002. Caché
Short Description: A married couple is terrorized by a series of surveillance videotapes left on their front porch.

Title: 3003. Suspicion
Short Description: A shy young heiress marries a charming gentleman, and soon begins to suspect he is planning to murder her.

Title: 3004. Bad Boy Bubby
Short Description: Bubby has spent thirty years trapped in the same small room, tricked by his mother. One day, he manages to escape and, deranged and naive in equal measures, his adventure into a modern and nihilistic life begins.

Title: 3005. Kiss of the Spider Woman
Short Description: A gay man and a political prisoner are together in a prison. The gay man narrates the stories of two fake movies and his own life.

Title: 3006. The Queen
Short Description: After the death of Princess Diana, Queen Elizabeth II struggles with her reaction to a sequence of events nobody could have predicted.

Title: 3007. Tess
Short Description: A strong-willed young peasant girl attracts the affection of two men.

Title: 3008. Shaun the Sheep Movie
Short Description: When Shaun decides to take the day off and have some fun, he gets a little more action than he bargained for. A mix up with the Farmer, a caravan and a very steep hill lead them all to the Big City and it's up to Shaun and the flock to return everyone safely to the green grass of home.

Title: 3009. Marshall
Short Description: The story of Thurgood Marshall, the crusading lawyer who would become the first African-American Supreme Court Justice, as he battles through one of his career-defining cases.

Title: 3010. Broadcast News
Short Description: A high-strung news producer finds herself in a love triangle between a talented but self-doubting reporter and a charming new anchor, who embodies the growing trivialization of news that she is determined to fight against.

Title: 3011. Reds
Short Description: A radical American journalist becomes involved with the Communist revolution in Russia, and hopes to bring its spirit and idealism to the United States.

Title: 3012. Deconstructing Harry
Short Description: Suffering from writer's block and eagerly awaiting his writing award, Harry Block remembers events from his past and scenes from his best-selling books as characters, real and fictional, come back to haunt him.

Title: 3013. Pusher II
Short Description: Tonny is released from prison - again. This time he has his mind set on changing his broken down life, but that is easier said than done.

Title: 3014. A Shot in the Dark
Short Description: Bumbling Inspector Jacques Clouseau falls in love with murder suspect Maria Gambrelli and tries to clear her name.

Title: 3015. Get Carter
Short Description: When his brother dies under mysterious circumstances in a car accident, London gangster Jack Carter travels to Newcastle to investigate.

Title: 3016. Topsy-Turvy
Short Description: Set in the 1880s, chronicles how during a creative dry spell, the partnership of the legendary musical/theatrical writers Gilbert and Sullivan almost dissolves, before they turn it all around and write the Mikado.

Title: 3017. 24 Hour Party People
Short Description: In 1976, Tony Wilson sets up Factory Records and brings Manchester's music to the world.

Title: 3018. 20th Century Women
Short Description: In 1979 Santa Barbara, Dorothea is a determined single mother who is raising her son, Jamie. Dorothea enlists the help of two women -- Abbie, a free-spirited punk artist and Julie, a savvy teenager -- to help with Jamie's upbringing.

Title: 3019. Gods and Monsters
Short Description: The last days of Frankenstein (1931) director James Whale are explored.

Title: 3020. Live Flesh
Short Description: After leaving jail, Víctor is still in love with Elena, but she's married to the former cop -now basketball player- who became paralysed by a shot from Víctor's gun...

Title: 3021. Girl in the Picture
Short Description: A young mother's mysterious death and her son's subsequent kidnapping blow open a decades-long mystery about the woman's true identity and the murderous federal fugitive at the center of it all.

Title: 3022. The Wanderers
Short Description: The Wanderers is a teenage, Italian gang in Bronx, NYC, 1963. They have their confrontations with other gangs. Drugs and weapons are uncool. Adult life awaits them.

Title: 3023. Beau Travail
Short Description: An ex-Foreign Legion officer recalls his once-glorious life of leading troops in Djibouti.

Title: 3024. Mona Lisa
Short Description: A man recently released from prison manages to get a job driving a call girl from customer to customer.

Title: 3025. Death in Venice
Short Description: While recovering in Venice, sickly composer Gustav von Aschenbach becomes dangerously fixated with teenager Tadzio.

Title: 3026. Angela's Ashes
Short Description: An Irish Catholic family returns to 1930s Limerick after a child's death in America. The unemployed I.R.A. veteran father struggles with poverty, prejudice and alcoholism as the family endures harsh slum conditions.

Title: 3027. Waterloo
Short Description: Facing the decline of everything he has worked to obtain, conqueror Napoleon Bonaparte and his army confront the British at the Battle of Waterloo.

Title: 3028. Transamerica
Short Description: A transgender woman takes an unexpected journey when she learns that she had a son, now a teenage runaway hustling on the streets of New York.

Title: 3029. Irma la Douce
Short Description: When a policeman falls in love with a prostitute, he doesn't want her to see other men, so he creates an alter-ego who will be her only customer.

Title: 3030. The Shadow in My Eye
Short Description: The fates of several Copenhagen residents collide when a WWII bombing mission accidentally targets a school full of children.

Title: 3031. Red Cliff
Short Description: The first chapter of a two-part story centered on a battle fought in China's Three Kingdoms period (220-280 A.D.).

Title: 3032. Ghajini
Short Description: A short-term memory loss patient goes on a killing spree in order to avenge the death of his ladylove.

Title: 3033. Point Blank
Short Description: After being double-crossed and left for dead, a mysterious man named Walker single-mindedly tries to retrieve the money that was stolen from him.

Title: 3034. Theri
Short Description: When his daughter's life is endangered by a local gang, Joseph Kuruvilla will do whatever it takes to stop them. However, at the same time, his dangerous past slowly resurfaces.

Title: 3035. The Girl Who Kicked the Hornet's Nest
Short Description: Lisbeth is recovering in a hospital and awaiting trial for three murders when she is released. Mikael must prove her innocence, but Lisbeth must be willing to share the details of her sordid experiences with the court.

Title: 3036. Lorenzo's Oil
Short Description: Lorenzo Odone, a Virginia 5-year-old, develops a degenerative nerve disease so rare that nobody is working on a cure, so his parents decide to immerse themselves in research and tackle the problem themselves.

Title: 3037. Red Dog
Short Description: Based on the legendary true story of the Red Dog who united a disparate local community while roaming the Australian outback in search of his long lost master.

Title: 3038. Jin-Roh: The Wolf Brigade
Short Description: A traumatized member of an elite para-military police force falls for the sister of a female terrorist courier who died in front of him on duty.

Title: 3039. The Professionals
Short Description: An arrogant Texas millionaire hires four adventurers to rescue his kidnapped wife from a notorious Mexican bandit.

Title: 3040. My Favorite Wife
Short Description: Missing for seven years and presumed dead, a woman returns home on the very day that her husband remarries.

Title: 3041. In Harm's Way
Short Description: A Naval officer, reprimanded after Pearl Harbor, is later promoted to Rear Admiral and gets a second chance to prove himself against the Japanese.

Title: 3042. Rosencrantz & Guildenstern Are Dead
Short Description: Two minor characters from the play 'Hamlet' stumble around unaware of their scripted lives and unable to deviate from them.

Title: 3043. A Star Is Born
Short Description: Young Esther Victoria Blodgett comes to Hollywood with dreams of stardom and achieves them only with the help of alcoholic leading man Norman Maine, whose best days are behind him.

Title: 3044. Dogfight
Short Description: Before leaving to fight in Vietnam, a group of teenagers play a game where they try to seduce the ugliest girl they can find.

Title: 3045. The Man from Laramie
Short Description: Newcomer Will Lockhart defies the local cattle baron and his sadistic son by working for one of his oldest rivals.

Title: 3046. Toni Erdmann
Short Description: A practical joking father tries to reconnect with his hard working daughter by creating an outrageous alter ego and posing as her CEO's life coach.

Title: 3047. Two Is a Family
Short Description: A bachelor enjoys his sweet life on the French Riviera until a one-night stand tells him, he's dad to Gloria and leaves her with him. He moves to London with Gloria. Mom turns up 8 years later.

Title: 3048. Midnight Runners
Short Description: Two friends who are students at Korean National Police University, find themselves in an endless race against time after they witness a kidnapping and decide to use their knowledge.

Title: 3049. The Best of Enemies
Short Description: Civil rights activist Ann Atwater faces off against C.P. Ellis, Exalted Cyclops of the Ku Klux Klan, in 1971 Durham, North Carolina over the issue of school integration.

Title: 3050. Bacurau
Short Description: After the death of her grandmother, Teresa comes home to her matriarchal village in a near-future Brazil to find a succession of sinister events that mobilizes all of its residents.

Title: 3051. Father Goose
Short Description: During World War II, a man persuaded to live on an isolated island and spot aircraft finds himself responsible for a teacher and several students, all female.

Title: 3052. Trade
Short Description: Adriana, 13, is kidnapped in Mexico City by Russian sex traffickers. Her criminal 17 y.o. brother starts looking for her. Across the border in Texas, he gets help from a cop.

Title: 3053. Uncle Frank
Short Description: In 1973, when Frank Bledsoe and his 18-year-old niece Beth take a road trip from Manhattan to Creekville, South Carolina, for the family patriarch's funeral, they're unexpectedly joined by Frank's lover, Walid.

Title: 3054. The Three Burials of Melquiades Estrada
Short Description: Ranch foreman Pete Perkins looks to fulfill the promise to his recently deceased best friend by burying him in his hometown in Mexico.

Title: 3055. Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo
Short Description: After growing up enduring criticism from his father, a young man finds his world shaken upon learning he was switched at birth with a millionaire's son.

Title: 3056. The Stranger
Short Description: An investigator from the War Crimes Commission travels to Connecticut to find an infamous Nazi.

Title: 3057. Abbott and Costello Meet Frankenstein
Short Description: The Wolf Man tries to warn a dimwitted porter that Dracula wants his brain for Frankenstein monster's body.

Title: 3058. The Day of the Beast
Short Description: Bent on committing as many sins as possible to avert the birth of the beast, a Catholic priest teams up with a Black Metal aficionado and an Italian connoisseur of the occult. Now, he must become an unrelenting sinner. Is there still hope?

Title: 3059. Shadowlands
Short Description: C.S. Lewis, a world-renowned Christian theologian, writer and professor, leads a passionless life until he meets spirited poet Joy Gresham from the U.S.

Title: 3060. You're Not You
Short Description: A drama centered on a classical pianist who has been diagnosed with ALS and the brash college student who becomes her caregiver.

Title: 3061. Pom Poko
Short Description: A community of magical shape-shifting raccoon dogs struggle to prevent their forest home from being destroyed by urban development.

Title: 3062. Desert Flower
Short Description: Waris Dirie, born 1965 in Somalia, flees at thirteen when sold to be a mans fourth wife. She works as a maid at the Somalian embassy in London, then in a McDonald's where she's discovered and becomes an international top model.

Title: 3063. The Beast of War
Short Description: A Soviet tank and its warring crew become separated from their patrol and lost in an Afghan valley with a group of vengeance-seeking rebels on their tracks.

Title: 3064. The Yellow Sea
Short Description: When the attempt to kill a professor goes wrong, a series of violent events are triggered which force a taxi driver to run for his life.

Title: 3065. Metropolitan
Short Description: A group of young upper-class Manhattanites are blithely passing through the gala debutante season, when an unusual outsider joins them and stirs them up.

Title: 3066. Grand Hotel
Short Description: A group of very different individuals staying at a luxurious hotel in Berlin deal with each of their respective dramas.

Title: 3067. The Innocents
Short Description: 1945. Mathilde is a French Red Cross doctor working on a mission to help the French survivors of the German camps. While she works in Poland, she is asked for help by a nun. In her convent, several nuns are pregnant.

Title: 3068. Pusher III
Short Description: Milo tries to be a family man and run his criminal organization, but a wrong drug shipment endangers everything.

Title: 3069. The Baader Meinhof Complex
Short Description: A look at Germany's terrorist group, The Red Army Faction (RAF), which organized bombings, robberies, kidnappings, and assassinations in the late 1960s and '70s.

Title: 3070. Ronia: The Robber's Daughter
Short Description: Ronja, the only child of robber chief Mattis must learn to survive the dangers of her local wilderness. In secret she also befriends Birk, the son of a rivaling robber Borka.

Title: 3071. Village of the Damned
Short Description: In the English village of Midwich, the blonde-haired, glowing-eyed children of uncertain paternity prove to have frightening powers.

Title: 3072. Tender Mercies
Short Description: A broken-down, middle-aged country singer gets a new wife, reaches out to his long-lost daughter, and tries to put his troubled life back together.

Title: 3073. The Last Black Man in San Francisco
Short Description: A young man searches for home in the changing city that seems to have left him behind.

Title: 3074. Keith
Short Description: Natalie, head of her curriculum activities in high school and riding on a tennis scholarship for college, gets Keith as her Chemistry lab partner. As Natalie can be uptight, Keith proves to be the opposite, even while hiding a secret.

Title: 3075. Atlantic City
Short Description: In a corrupt city, a small-time gangster and the estranged wife of a pot dealer find themselves thrown together in an escapade of love, money, drugs and danger.

Title: 3076. Nil by Mouth
Short Description: A rough, short-tempered patriarch of a working-class family sees his life and the relationships around him slowly unravel.

Title: 3077. The Man with the Golden Arm
Short Description: A junkie must face his true self to kick his drug addiction.

Title: 3078. Barney's Version
Short Description: The picaresque and touching story of the politically incorrect, fully lived life of the impulsive, irascible and fearlessly blunt Barney Panofsky.

Title: 3079. Norma Rae
Short Description: A young single mother and textile worker agrees to help unionize her mill despite the problems and dangers involved.

Title: 3080. Shanghai Express
Short Description: A notorious woman rides a train through a dangerous situation with a British captain she loved.

Title: 3081. Richard III
Short Description: The classic Shakespearean play about the murderously scheming 15th-century king is reimagined in an alternative setting of 1930s England as clouds of fascism gather.

Title: 3082. The Spanish Apartment
Short Description: A strait-laced French student moves into an apartment in Barcelona with a cast of six other characters from all over Europe. Together, they speak the international language of love and friendship.

Title: 3083. A Woman Is a Woman
Short Description: A stripper who's desperate to become a mother accepts her reluctant boyfriend's suggestion that she be impregnated by his best friend.

Title: 3084. Holiday Inn
Short Description: At an inn which is open only on holidays, a crooner and a hoofer vie for the affections of a beautiful up-and-coming performer.

Title: 3085. Pumping Iron
Short Description: Arnold Schwarzenegger and Lou Ferrigno face off in a no-holds-barred competition for the title of Mr. Olympia in this critically-acclaimed film that made Schwarzenegger a household name.

Title: 3086. The Long, Hot Summer
Short Description: Accused barn burner and conman Ben Quick arrives in a small Mississippi town and quickly ingratiates himself with its richest family, the Varners.

Title: 3087. Hope and Glory
Short Description: A young boy living on the outskirts of London comes of age during the uncertain days of World War II.

Title: 3088. Written on the Wind
Short Description: Alcoholic playboy Kyle Hadley marries the woman secretly loved by his poor but hard-working best friend, who in turn is pursued by Kyle's sister.

Title: 3089. In the House
Short Description: A high school French teacher is drawn into a precocious student's increasingly transgressive story about his relationship with a friend's family.

Title: 3090. Detour
Short Description: The life of Al Roberts, a pianist in a New York nightclub, turns into a nightmare when he decides to hitchhike to Los Angeles to visit his girlfriend.

Title: 3091. Bajirao Mastani
Short Description: An account of the romance between the Maratha general, Baji Rao I and Mastani, princess of Bundelkhand.

Title: 3092. The Front Page
Short Description: A ruthless editor tries to get his top reporter to cover one more crime story before retirement.

Title: 3093. The Monster
Short Description: After a series of bizarre actions, Loris is mistaken for a serial killer. Jessica, a policewoman in undercover, will try to induce him to commit a murder.

Title: 3094. On the Town
Short Description: Three sailors wreak havoc as they search for love during a whirlwind 24-hour leave in New York City.

Title: 3095. The In-Laws
Short Description: On the eve of their children's marriage, NYC in-laws Sheldon Kornpett and Vince Ricardo embark on a series of misadventures involving the CIA, the Treasury Department and Central American dictators.

Title: 3096. Hilary and Jackie
Short Description: The tragic story of world renowned classic cellist Jacqueline du Pré, as told from the point of view of her sister, flautist Hilary du Pré-Finzi.

Title: 3097. Brigsby Bear
Short Description: After being freed from his life in an underground bunker, a man sets out to make a movie of the only TV show he has ever known.

Title: 3098. Two Days, One Night
Short Description: Liège, Belgium. Sandra is a factory worker who discovers that her workmates have opted for a EUR1,000 bonus in exchange for her dismissal. She has only a weekend to convince her colleagues to give up their bonuses in order to keep her job.

Title: 3099. The Collector
Short Description: A womanizing art dealer and a painter find the serenity of their Riviera vacation disturbed by a third guest, a vivacious bohemian woman known for her long list of male conquests.

Title: 3100. Christmas in Connecticut
Short Description: A food writer who has lied about being the perfect housewife must try to cover her deception when her boss and a returning war hero invite themselves to her home for a traditional family Christmas.

Title: 3101. My Favorite Year
Short Description: An aging, dissolute matinee idol is slated to appear on a live TV variety show in 1954, and a young comedy writer is tasked with the thankless job of keeping him ready and sober for the broadcast.

Title: 3102. Kho Gaye Hum Kahan
Short Description: Ahana, Neil and Imaad are three friends in their 20s trying to find meaning in the digital age. They lean on each other as they navigate complexities of relationships and self-discovery.

Title: 3103. Read My Lips
Short Description: She is almost deaf and he lip-reads. He is an ex-convict. She wants to help him. He thinks no one can help except himself.

Title: 3104. Monsoon Wedding
Short Description: A stressed father, a bride-to-be with a secret, a smitten event planner, and relatives from around the world create much ado about the preparations for an arranged marriage in India.

Title: 3105. Roma
Short Description: A fluid, unconnected and sometimes chaotic procession of scenes detailing the various people and events of life in Italy's capital, most of it based on director Federico Fellini's life.

Title: 3106. City Island
Short Description: Prison guard Vince tells Molly from acting class, that one inmate is his 24 y.o. love child. Vince takes him home to stay with his family - straight A son with fat girl fetish, college dropout/stripper daughter and cute wife.

Title: 3107. Phoenix
Short Description: After surviving Auschwitz, a former cabaret singer has her disfigured face reconstructed and returns to her war-ravaged hometown to seek out her gentile husband, who may or may not have betrayed her to the Nazis.

Title: 3108. Monsieur Hulot's Holiday
Short Description: Monsieur Hulot comes to a beachside hotel for a vacation and accidentally, but good-naturedly, causes havoc.

Title: 3109. In China They Eat Dogs
Short Description: Two brothers, one cold and ruthless, the other sensitive and reluctant, and their brutal misadventures.

Title: 3110. The Bélier Family
Short Description: A girl, who lives with her deaf parents, discovers that she has the gift of singing.

Title: 3111. Loft
Short Description: Five close friends, all of them married, share a loft to meet their mistresses. One day they find the body of a young woman in the loft. Since there are only five keys to the loft, the five men begin to suspect each other of murder.

Title: 3112. Sorry, Wrong Number
Short Description: When neurotic bedridden wife Leona Stevenson overhears a murder plot on her telephone, she tries to piece the puzzle together and prevent the murder. Based on Lucille Fletcher's famous radio play.

Title: 3113. Manhattan Murder Mystery
Short Description: Middle-aged New York married couple Larry and Carol Lipton suspect foul play when their neighbor Paul House's wife Lillian suddenly drops dead.

Title: 3114. Bullhead
Short Description: Sint-Truiden, Belgium. Jacky, a young cattle farmer who is constantly pumped on steroids and hormones, is approached by a veterinarian to make a deal with a notorious beef trader.

Title: 3115. Shogun Assassin
Short Description: When the wife of the Shogun's Decapitator is murdered and he is ordered to commit suicide by the paranoid Shogun, he and his four-year-old son escape and become assassins for hire, embarking on a journey of blood and violent death.

Title: 3116. The Scent of Green Papaya
Short Description: A Vietnamese servant girl, Mui, observes lives within two different Saigon families: the first, a woman textile seller with three boys and a frequently absent husband; the second, a handsome young pianist with his fiancée.

Title: 3117. Interiors

Title: 3282. The Prince of Egypt

Title: 3283. The Outfit
Short Description: An expert cutter must outwit a dangerous group of mobsters in order to survive a fateful night.

Title: 3284. Good Luck to You, Leo Grande
Short Description: Nancy Stokes, a retired school teacher, is yearning for some adventure, and some sex. And she has a plan, which involves hiring a young sex worker named Leo Grande.

Title: 3285. Murder on the Orient Express
Short Description: In December 1935, when his transcontinental luxury train is stranded by deep snow, detective Hercule Poirot is called on to solve a murder that occurred in his car the night before, with a multitude of suspects.

Title: 3286. The Birdcage
Short Description: A gay cabaret owner and his drag queen companion agree to put up a false straight front so that their son can introduce them to his fiancée's right-wing, conservative parents.

Title: 3287. Michael Clayton
Short Description: A law firm brings in its "fixer" to remedy the situation after a lawyer has a breakdown while representing a chemical company that he knows is guilty in a multibillion-dollar class action suit.

Title: 3288. Mask
Short Description: A teenager with a massive facial skull deformity and biker gang mother attempt to live as normal a life as possible under the circumstances.

Title: 3289. The Crying Game
Short Description: A British soldier kidnapped by the IRA soon befriends one of his captors, who then becomes drawn into the soldier's world.

Title: 3290. Treasure Planet
Short Description: Jim Hawkins is a teenager who finds the map of a great treasure hidden by a space pirate. Together with some friends, he sets off in a large spaceship, shaped like a caravel, on his quest.

Title: 3291. Fracture
Short Description: After shooting his wife, Ted confesses his crime and asks the court to move his case to trial. He represents himself against Willy, a successful lawyer. But there's more to the case than meets the eye.

Title: 3292. Manhunter
Short Description: Former FBI profiler Will Graham returns to service to pursue a deranged serial killer dubbed "the Tooth Fairy" by the media.

Title: 3293. Videodrome
Short Description: A programmer at a Toronto TV station that specializes in adult entertainment searches for the producers of a dangerous and bizarre broadcast.

Title: 3294. Silverado
Short Description: A band of misfit friends come together to right the injustices which exist in a small town.

Title: 3295. The Wolf Man
Short Description: Upon his return to his father's estate, aristocrat Larry Talbot meets a beautiful woman, attends a mystical carnival and uncovers a horrifying curse.

Title: 3296. Belfast
Short Description: A young boy and his working-class Belfast family experience the tumultuous late 1960s.

Title: 3297. Layer Cake
Short Description: A successful cocaine dealer gets two tough assignments from his boss on the eve of his planned early retirement.

Title: 3298. Sex, Lies, and Videotape
Short Description: A sexually repressed woman's husband is having an affair with her sister. The arrival of a visitor with a rather unusual fetish changes everything.

Title: 3299. The Founder
Short Description: The story of Ray Kroc, a salesman who turned two brothers' innovative fast food eatery, McDonald's, into the biggest restaurant business in the world, with a combination of ambition, persistence, and ruthlessness.

Title: 3300. Only Lovers Left Alive
Short Description: A depressed musician reunites with his lover. However, their romance, which has already endured several centuries, is disrupted by the arrival of her uncontrollable younger sister.

Title: 3301. In the Heights
Short Description: In Washington Heights, a sympathetic New York bodega owner saves every penny every day as he imagines and sings about a better life.

Title: 3302. The Mighty
Short Description: Kevin suffers from a Morquio's syndrome, which weakens his heart and stunts his growth. Maxwell has dyslexia and towers above his classmates. The two couldn't be more different, but, when Kevin is asked to help Maxwell, they soon bond.

Title: 3303. The Post
Short Description: A cover-up spanning four U.S. Presidents pushes the country's first female newspaper publisher and her editor to join an unprecedented battle between press and government.

Title: 3304. The Fountain
Short Description: As a modern-day scientist, Tommy is struggling with mortality, desperately searching for the medical breakthrough that will save the life of his cancer-stricken wife, Izzi.

Title: 3305. The Italian Job
Short Description: A comic caper movie about a plan to steal a gold shipment from the streets of Turin by creating a traffic jam.

Title: 3306. The Bank Job
Short Description: Martine offers Terry a lead on a foolproof bank hit on London's Baker Street. She targets a roomful of safe deposit boxes worth millions in cash and jewelry along with a treasure trove of dirty secrets.

Title: 3307. Cactus Flower
Short Description: A dentist pretends to be married to avoid commitment, but when he falls for his girlfriend and proposes, he must recruit his lovelorn nurse to pose as his wife.

Title: 3308. Chocolat
Short Description: Single mother Vianne Rocher and her young daughter arrive in a rural French town in the winter of 1959, and open an unusual chocolate shop that disrupts the moral fiber of the strictly Catholic townsfolk and mayor.

Title: 3309. Monsters University
Short Description: A look at the relationship between Mike Wazowski and James P. "Sully" Sullivan during their days at Monsters University, when they weren't necessarily the best of friends.

Title: 3310. Ronin
Short Description: A freelancing former U.S. Intelligence Agent tries to track down a mysterious package that is wanted by the Irish and the Russians.

Title: 3311. Angel Heart
Short Description: In 1955 New Orleans, small-time private investigator Harry Angel is hired by a man who calls himself Louis Cypher to track down a singer named Johnny Favorite, but the investigation takes an unexpected and somber turn.

Title: 3312. Bitter Moon
Short Description: After hearing stories of her, a passenger on a cruise ship develops an irresistible infatuation with an eccentric paraplegic's wife.

Title: 3313. Vice
Short Description: The story of Dick Cheney, an unassuming bureaucratic Washington insider, who quietly wielded immense power as Vice President to George W. Bush, reshaping the country and the globe in ways that are still felt today.

Title: 3314. Strange Days
Short Description: A former cop turned street-hustler accidentally uncovers a conspiracy in Los Angeles in 1999.

Title: 3315. Finding Dory
Short Description: Friendly but forgetful blue tang Dory begins a search for her long-lost parents and everyone learns a few things about the real meaning of family along the way.

Title: 3316. The Courier
Short Description: Businessman Greville Wynne is asked by a Russian source to try to help put an end to the Cuban Missile Crisis.

Title: 3317. RocknRolla
Short Description: When a Russian mobster orchestrates a crooked land deal, millions of dollars are up for grabs, drawing in the entire London underworld into a feeding frenzy at a time when the old criminal regime is losing turf to a wealthy foreign mob.

Title: 3318. Lawless
Short Description: Set in Depression-era Franklin County, Virginia, a trio of bootlegging brothers are threatened by a new special deputy and other authorities angling for a cut of their profits.

Title: 3319. A Beautiful Day in the Neighborhood
Short Description: Lloyd Vogel, a cynical journalist, gets acquainted with a kind-hearted television presenter, Fred Rogers, while writing an article on him. With time, the two strike an unlikely friendship.

Title: 3320. Easy Rider
Short Description: Two bikers head from L.A. to New Orleans through the open country and desert lands, and along the way they meet a man who bridges a counter-culture gap of which they had been unaware.

Title: 3321. The Hitcher
Short Description: A young man who escapes the clutches of a murderous hitchhiker is subsequently stalked by the hitcher and framed for his crimes.

Title: 3322. Top Secret!
Short Description: An American rock and roll singer is invited to a cultural festival in East Germany in order to distract from a plot to destroy NATO submarines, but he accidentally becomes involved in a resistance plot to rescue an imprisoned scientist.

Title: 3323. A Dog's Purpose
Short Description: A dog discovers the meaning of its own existence through the lives of the humans it teaches to laugh and love. Reincarnated as multiple canines over the course of five decades, the lovable pooch develops an unbreakable bond with Ethan.

Title: 3324. Swingers
Short Description: A wannabe actor has a hard time moving on from a break-up, but he is lucky to have supportive friends.

Title: 3325. We Were Soldiers
Short Description: The story of the first major battle of the American phase of the Vietnam War, and the soldiers on both sides that fought it, while their wives wait nervously and anxiously at home for the good news or the bad news.

Title: 3326. Election
Short Description: A high school teacher meets his match in an over-achieving student politician.

Title: 3327. The Age of Innocence
Short Description: A tale of nineteenth-century New York high society in which a young lawyer falls in love with a woman separated from her husband, while he is engaged to the woman's cousin.

Title: 3328. Frailty
Short Description: A mysterious man arrives at the offices of an FBI agent and recounts his childhood: how his religious fanatic father received visions telling him to destroy people who were in fact "demons."

Title: 3329. The Darjeeling Limited
Short Description: A year after their father's funeral, three brothers travel across India by train in an attempt to bond with each other.

Title: 3330. Somewhere in Time
Short Description: A Chicago playwright uses self-hypnosis to travel back in time and meet the actress whose vintage portrait hangs in a grand hotel.

Title: 3331. State of Grace
Short Description: An undercover officer rejoins Irish mob pals in Hell's Kitchen.

Title: 3332. The Unbearable Lightness of Being
Short Description: A doctor in 1968 Prague struggles with monogamy to his wife's frustration, and then the Soviet invasion further disrupts their lives.

Title: 3333. Quills
Short Description: In a Napoleonic era insane asylum, an inmate, the irrepressible Marquis De Sade, fights a battle of wills against a tyrannically prudish doctor.

Title: 3334. In the Line of Fire
Short Description: Secret Service agent Frank Horrigan couldn't save Kennedy, but he's determined not to let a clever assassin take out this president.

Title: 3335. A Room with a View
Short Description: Lucy Honeychurch shares a brief romance with George Emerson in Florence. Yet as she tries to move on with her life and look for marriage elsewhere, can she truly forget the events of that summer?

Title: 3336. Muriel's Wedding
Short Description: A young social outcast in Australia steals money from her parents to finance a vacation where she hopes to find happiness, and perhaps love.

Title: 3337. The Doors
Short Description: Jim Morrison's life, from his LA film student days to his death in Paris. Val Kilmer delivers an uncanny portrayal, with vocals indistinguishable from Morrison's originals. It depicts Morrison's journey as the iconic 60s rock frontman.

Title: 3338. Papillon
Short Description: Wrongfully convicted for murder, Henri Charriere forms an unlikely relationship with fellow inmate and quirky convicted counterfeiter, Louis Dega, in an attempt to escape from the notorious penal colony on Devil's Island.

Title: 3339. The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie
Short Description: SpongeBob takes leave from Bikini Bottom in order to track down, with Patrick, King Neptune's stolen crown.

Title: 3340. Rise of the Guardians
Short Description: When the evil spirit Pitch launches an assault on Earth, the Immortal Guardians team up to protect the innocence of children all around the world.

Title: 3341. The Full Monty
Short Description: Six unemployed steel workers form a male striptease act. The women cheer them on to go for "the full monty" - total nudity.

Title: 3342. The Life Aquatic with Steve Zissou
Short Description: With a plan to exact revenge on a legendary shark that killed his partner, oceanographer Steve Zissou (Bill Murray) rallies a crew that includes his estranged wife, a journalist, and a man who may or may not be his son.

Title: 3343. Steve Jobs
Short Description: Steve Jobs takes us behind the scenes of the digital revolution, to paint a portrait of the man at its epicenter. The story unfolds backstage at three iconic product launches, ending in 1998 with the unveiling of the iMac.

Title: 3344. Sleeping Beauty
Short Description: After being snubbed by the royal family, a malevolent fairy places a curse on a princess which only a prince can break, along with the help of three good fairies.
In 1971, a young and disoriented British soldier is accidentally abandoned by his unit following a riot on the deadly streets of Belfast.

Title: 3346. The Parent Trap
Short Description: Teenage twin sisters swap places and scheme to reunite their divorced parents.

Title: 3347. Spirit: Stallion of the Cimarron
Short Description: A captured mustang remains determined to return to his herd no matter what.

Title: 3348. St. Vincent
Short Description: A young boy whose parents have just divorced finds an unlikely friend and mentor in the misanthropic, bawdy, hedonistic war veteran who lives next door.

Title: 3349. Slap Shot
Short Description: A failing ice hockey team finds success with outrageously violent hockey goonery.

Title: 3350. Force Majeure
Short Description: A family vacationing in the French Alps is confronted with a devastating avalanche.

Title: 3351. Team America: World Police
Short Description: Popular Broadway actor Gary Johnston is recruited by the elite counter-terrorism organization Team America: World Police. As the world begins to crumble around him, he must battle with terrorists, celebrities and falling in love.

Title: 3352. The Witcher: Nightmare of the Wolf
Short Description: Escaping from poverty to become a witcher, Vesemir slays monsters for coin and glory, but when a new menace rises, he must face the demons of his past.

Title: 3353. A River Runs Through It
Short Description: Two sons of a stern minister - one reserved, one rebellious - grow up in rural 1920s Montana while devoted to fly fishing.

Title: 3354. The Rainmaker
Short Description: A newly minted lawyer who's just passed the bar exam takes on a fraudulent insurance company in a multi-million dollar lawsuit.

Title: 3355. The Book of Life
Short Description: Manolo, a young man who is torn between fulfilling the expectations of his family and following his heart, embarks on an adventure that spans three fantastic worlds where he must face his greatest fears.

Title: 3356. Chasing Amy
Short Description: Holden and Banky are comic book artists. Everything's going good for them until they meet Alyssa, also a comic book artist. Holden falls for her, but his hopes are crushed when he finds out she's a lesbian.

Title: 3357. The Fox and the Hound
Short Description: A fox named Tod and a hound named Copper vow to be best friends forever. But as Copper grows into a hunting dog, their unlikely friendship faces the ultimate test.

Title: 3358. War Horse
Short Description: A young farm boy enlists to serve in World War I after his beloved horse is sold to the cavalry. His hopeful journey takes him out of England and onto the front lines as the war rages on.

Title: 3359. Born on the Fourth of July
Short Description: The biography of Ron Kovic. Paralyzed in the Vietnam war, he becomes an anti-war and pro-human rights political activist after feeling betrayed by the country for which he fought.

Title: 3360. Star Trek VI: The Undiscovered Country
Short Description: On the eve of retirement, Kirk and McCoy are charged with assassinating the Klingon High Chancellor and imprisoned. The Enterprise crew must help them escape to thwart a conspiracy aimed at sabotaging the last best hope for peace.

Title: 3361. August: Osage County
Short Description: A look at the lives of the strong-willed women of the Weston family, whose paths have diverged until a family crisis brings them back to the Oklahoma house they grew up in, and to the dysfunctional woman who raised them.

Title: 3362. Mean Streets
Short Description: In New York City's Little Italy, a devoutly Catholic mobster must reconcile his desire for power, his feelings for his epileptic girlfriend, and his devotion to his troublesome friend.

Title: 3363. The Professor and the Madman
Short Description: Professor James Murray begins work compiling words for the first edition of the Oxford English Dictionary in the 19th century, and receives over 10,000 entries from a patient at Broadmoor Criminal Lunatic Asylum, Dr. William Minor.

Title: 3364. Horror of Dracula
Short Description: When Jonathan Harker rouses the ire of Count Dracula for accepting a job at the vampire's castle under false pretenses, his friend Dr. Van Helsing pursues the predatory villain.

Title: 3365. Living
Short Description: In 1950s London, a humorless bureaucrat decides to take time off work to experience life after receiving a grim diagnosis.

Title: 3366. Fences
Short Description: A working-class African-American father tries to raise his family in the 1950s, while coming to terms with the events of his life.

Title: 3367. The Ghost Writer
Short Description: A ghost writer, hired to complete the memoirs of a former British Prime Minister, uncovers secrets that put his own life in jeopardy.

Title: 3368. The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel
Short Description: British retirees travel to India to take up residence in what they believe is a newly restored hotel. Less luxurious than advertised, the Marigold Hotel nevertheless slowly begins to charm in unexpected ways.

Title: 3369. Angst
Short Description: A troubled man gets released from prison and starts taking out his sadistic fantasies on an unsuspecting family living in a secluded house.

Title: 3370. Dead Ringers
Short Description: Twin gynecologists take full advantage of the fact that nobody can tell them apart, until their relationship begins to deteriorate over a woman.

Title: 3371. The Good the Bad the Weird
Short Description: The story of two outlaws and a bounty hunter in 1940s Manchuria and their rivalry to possess a treasure map while being pursued by the Japanese army and Chinese bandits.

Title: 3372. Runaway Train
Short Description: Two escaped convicts and a female railway worker find themselves trapped on a speeding train with no brakes and nobody driving.

Title: 3373. Go
Short Description: The aftermath of a drug deal as told from three different points of view.

Title: 3374. Stuck in Love.
Short Description: An acclaimed writer, his ex-wife, and their teenaged children come to terms with the complexities of love in all its forms over the course of one tumultuous year.

Title: 3375. About Schmidt
Short Description: Newly retired from the insurance industry, Omaha native Warren Schmidt embarks on an RV journey to his estranged daughter Jeannie's wedding in Denver Colorado, only to discover more about himself and life than he ever expected.

Title: 3376. 20,000 Leagues Under the Sea
Short Description: A ship sent to investigate a wave of mysterious sinkings encounters the advanced submarine, the Nautilus, commanded by Captain Nemo.

Title: 3377. Candy
Short Description: A poet falls in love with an art student who gravitates to his bohemian lifestyle -- and his love of heroin. Hooked as much on one another as they are on the drug, their relationship alternates between states of oblivion, self-destruction, and despair.

Title: 3378. Anthropoid
Short Description: Based on the extraordinary true story of Operation Anthropoid, the WWII mission to assassinate SS General Reinhard Heydrich, the main architect behind the Final Solution and the Reich's third in command after Hitler and Himmler.

Title: 3379. The Secret Life of Bees
Short Description: 1964. Lily, a lonely teenager, flees from her home and reaches a small town in South Carolina. Once there, she finds herself in the company of the Boatwright sisters who introduce her to a new world.

Title: 3380. Christopher Robin
Short Description: A working-class family man, Christopher Robin, encounters his childhood friend Winnie-the-Pooh, who helps him to rediscover the joys of life.

Title: 3381. Vanishing Point
Short Description: During the 1970s, car-delivery driver Kowalski delivers hot rods in record time, but always runs into trouble.

Title: 3382. Ringu
Short Description: When her niece is found dead along with three friends after viewing a supposedly cursed videotape, reporter Reiko sets out to investigate. She finds the tape, watches it and receives a phone call informing her that she'll die in a week.

Title: 3383. Murder by Death
Short Description: Five famous literary detective characters and their sidekicks are invited to a bizarre mansion to solve an even stranger mystery.

Title: 3384. The Dead Zone
Short Description: A man awakens from a coma to discover he has a psychic ability to foresee future events.

Title: 3385. Mother and Child
Short Description: A drama centered around three women: A fifty-year-old woman, the daughter she gave up for adoption thirty-five years ago, and a woman looking to adopt a child of her own.

Title: 3386. Mongol: The Rise of Genghis Khan
Short Description: The story recounts the early life of Genghis Khan who was a slave before going on to conquer half the world in 1206.

Title: 3387. The Report
Short Description: Idealistic Senate staffer Daniel J. Jones, tasked by his boss to lead an investigation into the CIA's post 9/11 Detention and Interrogation Program, uncovers shocking secrets.

Title: 3388. Crazy Heart
Short Description: A faded country music musician is forced to reassess his dysfunctional life during a doomed romance that also inspires him.

Title: 3389. Men of Honor
Short Description: Carl Brashear is an ambitious sharecropper who joins the U.S. Navy to become the world's first black master diver. But as he works through diving training, the racist Master Chief sets out to make Carl's journey as difficult as possible.

Title: 3390. Speak
Short Description: A teenager is traumatized into silence after a disastrous summer party.

Title: 3391. Pay It Forward
Short Description: A young boy attempts to make the world a better place after his teacher gives him that chance.

Title: 3392. The Hudsucker Proxy
Short Description: A naive business graduate is installed as president of a manufacturing company as part of a stock scam.

Title: 3393. Till
Short Description: In 1955, after Emmett Till is murdered in a brutal lynching, his mother vows to expose the racism behind the attack while working to have those involved brought to justice.

Title: 3394. Drugstore Cowboy
Short Description: A pharmacy-robbing dope fiend and his crew pop pills and evade the law.

Title: 3395. El Topo
Short Description: A mysterious black-clad gunfighter wanders a mystical Western landscape encountering multiple bizarre characters.

Title: 3396. Compartment Number 6
Short Description: As a train weaves its way up to the arctic circle, two strangers share a journey that will change their perspective on life.

Title: 3397. An Education
Short Description: A coming-of-age story about a teenage girl in 1960s suburban London, and how her life changes with the arrival of a playboy nearly twice her age.

Title: 3398. The Transformers: The Movie
Short Description: The Autobots must stop a colossal planet-consuming robot who goes after the Autobot Matrix of Leadership. At the same time, they must defend themselves against an all-out attack from the Decepticons.

Title: 3399. Reversal of Fortune
Short Description: Wealthy Sunny von Bülow lies brain-dead, husband Claus guilty of attempted murder; but he says he's innocent and hires Alan Dershowitz for his appeal.

Title: 3400. Magnum Force
Short Description: Inspector "Dirty" Harry Callahan pursues a conspiracy of vigilante cops, who are not above going beyond the law to kill San Francisco's undesirables.

Title: 3401. Quadrophenia
Short Description: Jimmy Cooper loathes his dead-end job and his working-class parents. He seeks solace with his mod clique, scooter riding, and drugs, only to be disappointed.

Title: 3402. Arlington Road
Short Description: A man begins to suspect his neighbors are not what they appear to be and their secrets could be deadly.

Title: 3403. Wish Dragon
Short Description: Determined teen Din is longing to reconnect with his childhood best friend when he meets a wish-granting dragon who shows him the magic of possibilities.

Title: 3404. Django
Short Description: A coffin-dragging gunslinger and a prostitute become embroiled in a bitter feud between a Klan of Southern racists and a band of Mexican Revolutionaries.

Title: 3405. Fahrenheit 451
Short Description: In an oppressive future, a fireman whose duty is to destroy all books begins to question his task.

Title: 3406. Honey Boy
Short Description: A young actor's stormy childhood and early adult years as he struggles to reconcile with his father and deal with his mental health.

Title: 3407. The Man Who Knew Infinity
Short Description: The story of the life and academic career of the pioneer Indian mathematician, Srinivasa Ramanujan, and his friendship with his mentor, Professor G.H. Hardy.

Title: 3408. Animal Kingdom
Short Description: A seventeen-year-old navigates his survival amongst an explosive criminal family and the detective who thinks he can save him.

Title: 3409. Dumbo
Short Description: Ridiculed because of his enormous ears, a young circus elephant is assisted by a mouse to achieve his full potential.

Title: 3410. The Light Between Oceans
Short Description: A lighthouse keeper and his wife living off the coast of Western Australia raise a baby they rescue from a drifting rowing boat.

Title: 3411. Strictly Ballroom
Short Description: A maverick dancer risks his career by performing an unusual routine and sets out to succeed with a new partner.

Title: 3412. Dope
Short Description: Life changes for Malcolm, a geek who's surviving life in a tough neighborhood, after a chance invitation to an underground party leads him and his friends into a Los Angeles adventure.

Title: 3413. The Way of the Dragon
Short Description: A country bumpkin martial artist visits his relatives in Rome, Italy, where he must defend them and their restaurant against harassment from brutal gangsters.

Title: 3414. In the Valley of Elah
Short Description: A retired military investigator works with a police detective to uncover the truth behind his son's disappearance following his return from a tour of duty in Iraq.

Title: 3415. A Mighty Wind
Short Description: Mockumentary captures the reunion of 1960s folk trio the Folksmen as they prepare for a show at The Town Hall to memorialize a recently deceased concert promoter.

Title: 3416. Along With the Gods: The Two Worlds
Short Description: After a heroic death, a firefighter navigates the afterlife with the help of three guides.

Title: 3417. Wonder Boys
Short Description: An English Professor tries to deal with his wife leaving him, the arrival of his editor who has been waiting for his book for seven years, and the various problems that his friends and associates involve him in.

Title: 3418. Conviction
Short Description: A working mother puts herself through law school in an effort to represent her brother, who has been wrongfully convicted of murder and has exhausted his chances to appeal his conviction through public defenders.

Title: 3419. Love & Basketball
Short Description: Monica and Quincy love and play basketball together through many life challenges from childhood to adulthood.

Title: 3420. Pump Up the Volume
Short Description: Mark runs a pirate radio station and causes an uproar when he speaks his mind and enthralls fellow teens.

Title: 3421. The Misfits
Short Description: A divorcée falls for an over-the-hill cowboy who is struggling to maintain his romantically-independent lifestyle.

Title: 3422. The Outlaws
Short Description: Based on real events, this crime action film depicts a Seoul detective's attempts to keep peace while two Chinese-Korean gangs battle over turf in the neighborhood.

Title: 3423. Sleep Tight
Short Description: César is the superintendent of an apartment building and keeps very close tabs on the tenants. He secretly enjoys inflicting pain on others, and the occupant of apartment 5B will be his new target.

Title: 3424. Bad Boys
Short Description: Chicago crime kid, Mick O'Brien, is sent to reform school after accidentally killing a rival's kid brother.

Title: 3425. Columbus
Short Description: A Korean-born man finds himself stuck in Columbus, Indiana, where his architect father is in a coma. The man meets a young woman who wants to stay in Columbus with her mother, a recovering addict, instead of pursuing her own dreams.

Title: 3426. Old Yeller
Short Description: A teenage boy grows to love a stray yellow dog while helping his mother and younger brother run their Texas homestead while their father is away on a cattle drive. First thought to be good-for-nothing mutt, Old Yeller is soon beloved by all.

Title: 3427. The Beguiled
Short Description: While recuperating in a Confederate girls' boarding school, a Union soldier cons his way into each of the lonely women's hearts, causing them to turn on each other, and eventually, on him.

Title: 3428. Shallow Grave
Short Description: Three friends discover their new flatmate dead but loaded with cash.

Title: 3429. The Andromeda Strain
Short Description: Top scientists work feverishly in a secret, state-of-the-art laboratory to discover what killed the citizens of a small town and how the deadly contagion can be stopped.

Title: 3430. Rescued by Ruby
Short Description: Chasing his dream to join an elite K-9 unit, a state trooper partners with a fellow underdog: clever but naughty shelter pup Ruby.

Title: 3431. Paris, Je T'aime
Short Description: Through the neighborhoods of Paris, love is veiled, revealed, imitated, sucked dry, reinvented, and awakened.

Title: 3432. The Great Race
Short Description: In the early 20th century, heroic Leslie Gallant and his despicable rival Professor Fate engage in an epic automobile race from New York to Paris while enthusiastic suffragette Maggie Dubois enters the race to report on every step of it.

Title: 3433. The Tale
Short Description: A woman filming a documentary on childhood rape victims starts to question the nature of her childhood relationship with her riding instructor and running coach.

Title: 3434. Viy
Short Description: A young priest is ordered to preside over the wake of witch in a small old wooden church of a remote village. This means spending three nights alone with the corpse with only his faith to protect him.

Title: 3435. The Wife
Short Description: A wife questions her life choices as she travels to Stockholm to see her husband receive the Nobel Prize for Literature.

Title: 3436. Merry Christmas Mr. Lawrence
Short Description: During WWII, a British colonel tries to bridge the cultural divides between a British POW and the Japanese camp commander in order to avoid bloodshed.

Title: 3437. Arizona Dream
Short Description: A young New Yorker goes to Arizona where he finds freedom to both love and dream.

Title: 3438. The Siege of Jadotville
Short Description: Irish Commandant Pat Quinlan leads a stand off with troops against French and Belgian Mercenaries in the Congo during the early 1960s.

Title: 3439. The Young Victoria
Short Description: A dramatization of the turbulent first years of Queen Victoria's rule, and her enduring romance with Prince Albert.

Title: 3440. Breakfast on Pluto
Short Description: In the 1970s, a young trans woman, Patrick "Kitten" Braden, comes of age by leaving her Irish town for London, in part to look for her mother and in part because her gender identity is beyond the town's understanding.

Title: 3441. Fist of Fury
Short Description: During the Japanese occupation of Shanghai, the star pupil of a recently-deceased martial arts teacher battles a Japanese dojo which seeks the demise of his master's fighting school.

Title: 3442. Calamity Jane
Short Description: The story of Calamity Jane, her saloon, and her romance with Wild Bill Hickok.

Title: 3443. Polytechnique
Short Description: A dramatization of the 1989 Montréal Massacre, during which several female engineering students were murdered by an unstable misogynist.

Title: 3444. Wristcutters: A Love Story
Short Description: A film set in a strange afterlife way station that has been reserved for people who have committed suicide.

Title: 3445. The Brave Little Toaster
Short Description: A group of dated appliances embark on a journey to the city to find their master after being abandoned in a cabin in the woods.

Title: 3446. Testament of Youth
Short Description: A British woman recalls coming of age during World War I - a story of young love, the futility of war, and how to make sense of the darkest times.

Title: 3447. Scarecrow
Short Description: An ex-con drifter with a penchant for brawling is amused by a homeless ex-sailor, so they partner up as they head east together.

Title: 3448. Anomalisa
Short Description: A man crippled by the mundanity of his life experiences something out of the ordinary.

Title: 3449. Defending Your Life
Short Description: In an afterlife way-station resembling a major city, the lives of the recently deceased are examined in a court-like setting.

Title: 3450. Brian Banks
Short Description: A football player's dreams to play in the NFL are halted when he is wrongly convicted and sent to prison. Years later, he fights to clear his name within an unjust system.

Title: 3451. The Man from Snowy River

Title: 3560. In Your Name

Title: 3562. Batman: The Long Halloween, Part Two
Short Description: The killer known as Holiday continues to stalk the Falcone crime family while a new class of costumed criminal rises in Gotham City. Batman suspects that a former ally might be the serial killer.

Short Description: A crooked lawyer persuades his brother-in-law to feign a serious injury.

Title: 3564. Gentleman's Agreement
Short Description: A reporter pretends to be Jewish in order to cover a story on anti-Semitism, and personally discovers the true depths of bigotry and hatred.

Title: 3569. Table No. 21
