Title: 3574. Tape
Short Description: Three old high school friends meet in a Michigan motel room to dissect painful memories from their past.

Title: 3575. Tsotsi
Short Description: Six days in the violent life of a young Johannesburg gang leader.

Title: 3576. Fyre
Short Description: An exclusive behind the scenes look at the infamous unraveling of the Fyre music festival.

Title: 3577. The Other Side of Hope
Short Description: A poker-playing restaurateur and former traveling salesman befriends a group of refugees newly arrived to Finland.

Title: 3578. Lantana
Short Description: The relationships of four couples unravel after the discovery of a young woman's body in Lantana bush in suburban Sydney.

Title: 3579. Fat City

Title: 3580. The Uninvited

Title: 3582. Stardust Memories

Title: 3588. Modigliani

Title: 3589. Death Note: The Last Name

Title: 3595. Wild Bill

Title: 3597. Raat Akeli Hai
Short Description: Follows a small town cop who is summoned to investigate the death of a politician which gets complicated by the victim's secretive family and his own conflicted heart.

Title: 3599. NH 10

Title: 3600. Facing Windows
Short Description: Overburdened and stuck in a greying marriage, Giovanna takes to caring for the Jewish Holocaust survivor her husband brings home. As she begins to reflect on her life, she turns to the man who lives across from her ...

Title: 3601. The Wing or The Thigh?

After having agreed to appear on a talk show to show his skills in naming food and wine by taste, he is confronted with two disasters: his son wants to become a clown rather than a restaurant tester and he, the famous Charles Duchemin, has lost his taste.

Title: 3608. Heroic Losers

On a trip home from Rome, where he studies literature and lives with his boyfriend, Tommaso decides to tell his parents the truth about himself. But when he is finally ready to come out in front of the entire family, his older brother Antonio ruins his plans.

Title: 3615. Jolly LLB 2
Short Description: Jolly is a clumsy lawyer who is faced with representing the most critical court case of his career.

Title: 3616. The Book of Vision
Short Description: Eva, a mysterious doctor, searches for an answer to her urgent dilemma as she unravels Dr. Anmuth's Book of Vision. Stellan gets involved in her life and is forced to confront his own nature as she faces the biggest decision of her life.

Title: 3617. Rams
Short Description: In a remote Icelandic farming valley, two brothers who haven't spoken in 40 years have to come together in order to save what's dearest to them - their sheep.

Title: 3618. Amen.
Short Description: During WWII SS officer Kurt Gerstein tries to inform Pope Pius XII about Jews being sent to extermination camps. Young Jesuit priest Riccardo Fontana helps him in the difficult mission to inform the world.

Title: 3619. Broken Blossoms
Short Description: A frail waif, abused by her brutal boxer father in London's seedy Limehouse District, is befriended by a sensitive Chinese immigrant with tragic consequences.

Title: 3620. A Better Tomorrow II
Short Description: A restauranteur teams up with a police officer and his ex-con brother to avenge the death of a friend's daughter.

Title: 3621. What the Health
Short Description: An intrepid filmmaker on a journey of discovery as he uncovers possibly the largest health secret of our time and the collusion between industry, government, pharmaceutical and health organizations keeping this information from us.

Title: 3622. Into the Inferno
Short Description: An exploration of active volcanoes around the world.

Title: 3623. No One Killed Jessica
Short Description: A journalist, who is more of an activist teams up with the sister of a murdered model, as she gets interested in the case and wants to bring justice to her case.

Title: 3624. City of Men
Short Description: Best buddies Acerola and Laranjinha, about to turn 18, discover things about their missing fathers' pasts which will shatter their solid friendship, in the middle of a war between rival drug gangs from Rio's favelas.

Title: 3625. Angrezi Medium
Short Description: When his daughter decides to further her studies in London, a hardworking Rajasthani businessman does everything in power to make her dreams come true.

Title: 3626. Common Wealth
Short Description: The accidental discovery of a big fortune hidden in the apartment of a deceased man will fill the heart of a real estate agent with greed and dreams of a luxurious life, but the neighbours think otherwise.

Title: 3627. Before I Disappear
Short Description: At the lowest point of his life, Richie gets a call from his estranged sister, asking him to look after his 11-year old niece Sophia for a few hours.

Title: 3628. Band Baaja Baaraat
Short Description: Shruti and Bittoo become partners in their very own "Wedding planning ka bijness" in Delhi and in the process discover friendship, love and one another.

Title: 3629. The Man in the White Suit
Short Description: An altruistic chemist invents a fabric which resists wear and stain as a boon to humanity, but big business and labor realize it must be suppressed for economic reasons.

Title: 3630. The God of Cookery
Short Description: The most renowned and feared chef in the world loses his title of God of Cookery because of his pompous attitude. Humbled, he sets out to reclaim his title.

Title: 3631. Muhammad: The Messenger of God
Short Description: The events, trials and tribulations of the city of Makkah in 7th century AD.

Title: 3632. Salyut-7
Short Description: USSR, June 1985. Based on actual events. After contact with the Salyut 7 space station is lost, cosmonauts Vladimir Dzhanibekov and Viktor Savinykh dock with the empty, frozen craft, and bring her back to life.

Title: 3633. Batla House
Short Description: In 2008, a violent shootout with terror suspects leaves one police officer struggling to hunt down the fugitives and justify the police action.

Title: 3634. Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Movie
Short Description: Mike Nelson and his robot companions watch and give their comments about This Island Earth (1955).

Title: 3635. Human Capital
Short Description: The destinies of two families are irrevocably tied together after a cyclist is hit off the road by a jeep in the night before Christmas Eve.

Title: 3636. Pyaar Ka Punchnama 2
Short Description: After falling in love, three roommates experience changes in their lives.

Title: 3637. Johnny Stecchino
Short Description: A kindhearted but bumbling idiot who likes to steal bananas, is passed off for a snitch hiding from the mob.

Title: 3638. Ittefaq
Short Description: A detective seeks out the truth between two different stories of a crime scene.

Title: 3639. Starbuck
Short Description: As his lover announces her pregnancy, a fortysomething slacker receives other life-changing news: 142 people, all of them the result of artificial insemination, have filed a class action lawsuit against him, their biological father.

Title: 3640. Toilet: A Love Story
Short Description: A woman threatens to leave her husband unless he installs a toilet in their home. To win back her love and respect, he heads out on a journey to fight against the backward society.

Title: 3641. The Taste of Others
Short Description: The lives of 6 people over 35 in Rouen, France, and their relationship to each other.

Title: 3642. Asterix and Cleopatra
Short Description: Cleopatra decides to prove to Julius Caesar that her people are not decadent by building a palace in less than three months. When Cleopatra's architect asks the Gallic druid Getafix for help, Asterix and Obelix accompany him to Egypt.

Title: 3643. Theeb
Short Description: In the Ottoman province of Hijaz during World War I, a young Bedouin boy experiences a greatly hastened coming-of-age as he embarks on a perilous desert journey to guide a British officer to his secret destination.

Title: 3644. The Memory of a Killer
Short Description: Vincke and Verstuyft are the best detectives of the Antwerp police department. They are confronted with the murder on a leading executive and put all their effort to catch the murderer.

Title: 3645. Love Likes Coincidences
Short Description: Year 1977, a September morning in Ankara... Yilmaz tries to rush his pregnant wife Neriman to the hospital and he crashes into Omer's car. This accident causes Omer's pregnant wife Inci, who was in the back seat, to have a pre-term labor. The babies are born on the same day. They see each other for the first time.

Title: 3646. The Gilded Cage
Short Description: For thirty years now Maria and José Ribeiro have been living on the ground floor of a Haussmannian building in one of the most exclusive districts of Paris. Everybody loves this nice couple of Portuguese immigrants, Mario for being a topnotch caretaker, José, a construction site supervisor by trade, for helping to do all kinds of jobs in the house. So, the day Maria and José announce their wish to return to Portugal, everybody is crushed. No, they just can't let them do a thing like that...!

Title: 3647. Ponniyin Selvan: Part Two
Short Description: Arulmozhi Varman continues on his journey to become Rajaraja I, the greatest ruler of the historic Chola empire of south India.

Title: 3648. D-Day
Short Description: A team of experts dispatched to bring in The Most Wanted Man in India almost achieve the unthinkable ... until something goes horribly wrong.

Title: 3649. Shanghai
Short Description: Prime leader of a campaign against a big government project is killed in what appears to be a road accident. An IAS officer is ordered to probe the incident and the veils of falsehood begin to drop.

Title: 3650. Te3n
Short Description: A grandfather, a priest and a police officer investigate the case of a kidnapped child.

Title: 3651. Lammbock
Short Description: Stefan and Kai have good going business, self-grown cannabis screened as pizza delivering service. For now they only have to deal with aphids.

Title: 3652. Born Into Brothels: Calcutta's Red Light Kids
Short Description: Two documentary filmmakers chronicle their time in Sonagchi, Calcutta and the relationships they developed with children of prostitutes who work the city's notorious red light district.

Title: 3653. The Warrior
Short Description: 1375. Nine Koryo warriors, envoys exiled by Imperial China, battle to protect a Chinese Ming Princess from Mongolian troops.

Title: 3654. Tere Bin Laden
Short Description: A reporter casts a fake Bin Laden to act in his video message to America, so he can immigrate there.

Title: 3655. Mulk
Short Description: One family member tries to help her own family when they are trapped in a dark controversy.

Title: 3656. Business Man
Short Description: A highly ambitious man visits Mumbai with the notion of ruling the city. He turns into a local gangster and manages to become a powerful businessman, though, his intentions are not what they seem.

Title: 3657. We Are Legion: The Story of the Hacktivists
Short Description: A documentary on the workings and beliefs of the self-described "hacktivist" collective, Anonymous.

Title: 3658. Ghulam
Short Description: An amateur boxer runs errands for a local gangster but revolts against him after the gangster kills his friend and his conscience is awakened.

Title: 3659. Rashmi Rocket
Short Description: A small-town girl overcomes all societal barriers to become a national-level athlete, but her glory is hindered when she is asked to undergo a gender test.

Title: 3660. Sonic the Hedgehog 3
Short Description: Sonic, Knuckles, and Tails reunite against a powerful new adversary, Shadow, a mysterious villain with powers unlike anything they have faced before. With their abilities outmatched, Team Sonic must seek out an unlikely alliance.

Title: 3661. Alien: Romulus
Short Description: While scavenging the deep ends of a derelict space station, a group of young space colonists come face to face with the most terrifying life form in the universe.

Title: 3662. Challengers
Short Description: Tashi, a former tennis prodigy turned coach, transformed her husband into a champion. But to overcome a recent losing streak and redeem himself, he'll need to face off against his former best friend and Tashi's ex-boyfriend.

Title: 3663. The Apprentice
Short Description: The story of how a young Donald Trump started his real-estate business in 1970s and '80s New York with the helping hand of infamous lawyer Roy M. Cohn.

Title: 3664. Midsommar
Short Description: A couple travels to Northern Europe to visit a rural hometown's fabled Swedish mid-summer festival. What begins as an idyllic retreat quickly devolves into an increasingly violent and bizarre competition at the hands of a pagan cult.

Title: 3665. Strange Darling
Short Description: Nothing is what it seems when a twisted one-night stand spirals into a serial killer's vicious murder spree.

Title: 3666. Babylon
Short Description: A tale of outsized ambition and outrageous excess, it traces the rise and fall of multiple characters during an era of unbridled decadence and depravity in early Hollywood.

Title: 3667. Bank of Dave
Short Description: Based on the true-life experiences of Dave Fishwick; 'Bank of Dave' tells the story of how a working class Burnley man and self-made millionaire fought to set up a community bank.

Title: 3668. West Side Story
Short Description: An adaptation of the 1957 musical, West Side Story explores forbidden love and the rivalry between the Jets and the Sharks, two teenage street gangs of different ethnic backgrounds.

Title: 3669. Basic Instinct
Short Description: A violent police detective investigates a brutal murder that might involve a manipulative and seductive novelist.

Title: 3670. Glass Onion
Short Description: Tech billionaire Miles Bron invites his friends for a getaway on his private Greek island. When someone turns up dead, Detective Benoit Blanc is put on the case.

Title: 3671. The Dreamers
Short Description: A young American studying in Paris in 1968 strikes up a friendship with a French brother and sister. Set against the background of the '68 Paris student riots.

Title: 3672. The Mummy
Short Description: At an archaeological dig in the ancient city of Hamunaptra, an American serving in the French Foreign Legion accidentally awakens a mummy who begins to wreak havoc as he searches for the reincarnation of his long-lost love.

Title: 3673. Transformers
Short Description: An ancient struggle between two Cybertronian races, the heroic Autobots and the evil Decepticons, comes to Earth, with a clue to the ultimate power held by a teenager.

Title: 3674. Red Rooms
Short Description: A model becomes obsessed with a high-profile murder trial.

Title: 3675. Wrath of Man
Short Description: A mysteriously stoic character is hired as a security guard by a cash truck company responsible for transporting a lot of money around Los Angeles each week.

Title: 3676. Mean Girls
Short Description: Cady Heron is a hit with The Plastics, the A-list girl clique at her new school, until she makes the mistake of falling for Aaron Samuels, the ex-boyfriend of alpha Plastic Regina George.

Title: 3677. The Invisible Man
Short Description: When Cecilia's abusive ex takes his own life and leaves her his fortune, she suspects his death was a hoax. As a series of coincidences turn lethal, Cecilia works to prove that she is being hunted by someone nobody can see.

Title: 3678. Tropic Thunder
Short Description: Through a series of freak occurrences, a group of actors shooting a big-budget war movie are forced to become the soldiers they are portraying.

Title: 3679. Cashback
Short Description: After a painful breakup, Ben develops insomnia. To kill time, he starts working the late night shift at the local supermarket, where his artistic imagination runs wild.

Title: 3680. Pretty Woman
Short Description: Edward, a rich entrepreneur, hires Vivian, a prostitute, to accompany him to a few social events. Trouble ensues when he falls in love with her and they try to bridge the gap between their worlds.

Title: 3681. The Devil All the Time
Short Description: Sinister characters converge around a young man devoted to protecting those he loves in a postwar backwoods town teeming with corruption and brutality

Title: 3682. Beauty and the Beast
Short Description: A brave, beautiful, and brilliant young woman is imprisoned by a beast in his castle. Despite her fears, she learns to see beyond the beast's hideous exterior and realize the gentle heart of the true prince within him.

Title: 3683. Prey
Short Description: Naru, a skilled warrior of the Comanche Nation, fights to protect her tribe against one of the first highly-evolved Predators to land on Earth.

Title: 3684. Fast Times at Ridgemont High
Short Description: A group of SoCal high school students would rather ignore their studies and instead indulge in their teenage distractions.

Title: 3685. Bone Tomahawk
Short Description: In the Old West, a sheriff and his posse must rescue several townspeople from cave-dwelling cannibals.

Title: 3686. Licorice Pizza
Short Description: The story of Alana Kane and Gary Valentine growing up, running around and going through the treacherous navigation of first love in the San Fernando Valley, 1973.

Title: 3687. Snowpiercer
Short Description: In a future where a failed climate change experiment has killed all life except for the survivors who boarded the Snowpiercer (a train that travels around the globe), a new class system emerges.

Title: 3688. Man of Steel
Short Description: An alien child is evacuated from his dying world and sent to Earth to live among humans. His peace is threatened when other survivors of his home planet invade Earth.

Title: 3689. Pitch Perfect
Short Description: Beca, a freshman at Barden University, is cajoled into joining The Bellas, her school's all-girls singing group. Injecting some much needed energy into their repertoire, The Bellas take on their male rivals in a campus competition.

Title: 3690. Shooter
Short Description: An expert marksman living in exile, is coaxed back into action after learning of a plot to kill the president. Now on the run after being double crossed for the assasination attempt he was trying to prevent, he sets out for the real killer, and the truth.

Title: 3691. Deepwater Horizon
Short Description: A dramatization of the disaster in April 2010, when the offshore drilling rig called the Deepwater Horizon exploded, resulting in the worst oil spill in history.

Title: 3692. The Lobster
Short Description: In a dystopian near future, according to the laws of The City, single people are taken to The Hotel, where they are obliged to find a romantic partner in 45 days or they're transformed into beasts and sent off into The Woods.

Title: 3693. Talk to Me
Short Description: When a group of friends discover how to conjure spirits using an embalmed hand, they become hooked on the new thrill, until one of them goes too far and unleashes terrifying supernatural forces.

Title: 3694. Free Guy
Short Description: When Guy, a bank teller, learns that he is a non-player character in a bloodthirsty, open-world video game, he goes on to become the hero of the story and takes the responsibility of saving the world.

Title: 3695. Mrs. Doubtfire
Short Description: After a bitter divorce, an actor disguises himself as a female housekeeper to spend time with his children held in custody by his former wife.

Title: 3696. Iron Man 3
Short Description: When Tony Stark's world is torn apart by a formidable terrorist called the Mandarin, he starts an odyssey of rebuilding and retribution.

Title: 3697. Ghost
Short Description: After a young man is murdered, his spirit stays behind to warn his lover of impending danger, with the help of a reluctant psychic.

Title: 3698. Bad Times at the El Royale
Short Description: 1969. Four strangers check in at the El Royale Hotel. The hotel is deserted, staffed by a single desk clerk. Some of the new guests' reasons for being there are less than innocent and some are not who they appear to be.

Title: 3699. Real Steel
Short Description: In a near future where robot boxing is a top sport, a struggling ex-boxer feels he's found a champion in a discarded robot.

Title: 3700. About a Boy
Short Description: Will, who attends single parent meetings to woo women, meets Marcus, a troubled 12-year-old boy. As they become friends, Will learns to be responsible while he helps Marcus with his studies.

Title: 3701. Sing
Short Description: In a city of humanoid animals, a hustling theater impresario's attempt to save his theater with a singing competition becomes grander than he anticipates even as its finalists find that their lives will never be the same.

Title: 3702. The 40-Year-Old Virgin
Short Description: Goaded by his buddies, a nerdy guy who's never "done the deed" only finds the pressure mounting when he meets a single mother.

Title: 3703. Margin Call
Short Description: Follows the key people at an investment bank over a 24-hour period during the early stages of the 2008 financial crisis.

Title: 3704. Brave
Short Description: Determined to make her own path in life, Princess Merida defies a custom that brings chaos to her kingdom. Granted one wish, Merida must rely on her bravery and her archery skills to undo a beastly curse.

Title: 3705. The Ides of March
Short Description: A campaign press secretary becomes involved in a scandal that threatens his candidate's election chances.

Title: 3706. Coming to America
Short Description: An extremely pampered African prince travels to Queens, New York and goes undercover to find a wife that he can respect for her intelligence and strong will.

Title: 3707. There's Something About Mary
Short Description: A man gets a chance to meet up with his dream girl from high school, even though his date with her back then was a complete disaster.

Title: 3708. Blade
Short Description: A half-vampire, half-mortal man becomes a protector of the mortal race, while slaying evil vampires.

Title: 3709. Dirty Dancing
Short Description: Spending the summer at a Catskills resort with her family, Frances "Baby" Houseman falls in love with the camp's dance instructor, Johnny Castle.

Title: 3710. Forgetting Sarah Marshall
Short Description: Devastated Peter takes a Hawaiian vacation in order to deal with the recent break-up with his TV star girlfriend, Sarah. Little does he know, Sarah's traveling to the same resort as her ex - and she's bringing along her new boyfriend.

Title: 3711. Spaceballs
Short Description: A star-pilot for hire and his trusty sidekick must come to the rescue of a princess and save Planet Druidia from the clutches of the evil Spaceballs.

Title: 3712. The Mist
Short Description: After a massive thunderstorm, an eerie, unwavering fog descends upon a Maine community. Locals seek refuge in a grocery store from the monstrous creatures now roaming the countryside killing everyone they encounter.

Title: 3713. Brothers
Short Description: While on tour in Afghanistan, Sam's helicopter is shot down and he is presumed dead. Back home, it is his screw-up brother who looks after the family. Sam does return, but with a lot of excess baggage.

Title: 3714. Jumanji
Short Description: When two kids find and play a magical board game, they release a man trapped in it for decades - and a host of dangers that can only be stopped by finishing the game.

Title: 3715. Don't Breathe
Short Description: Three delinquents break into the house of a war veteran who is blind to steal his money. However, they discover that the man is not as defenseless as he seems.

Title: 3716. Red Rocket
Short Description: Washed-up porn star Mikey Saber returns to his small Texas hometown where nobody really wants him back.

Title: 3717. Gran Turismo
Short Description: Based on the unbelievable, inspiring true story of a team of underdogs - a struggling, working-class gamer, a failed former race car driver, and an idealistic motorsport exec - who risk it all to take on the most elite sport in the world.

Title: 3718. Melancholia
Short Description: Two sisters find their already strained relationship challenged as a mysterious new planet threatens to collide with Earth.

Title: 3719. Four Weddings and a Funeral
Short Description: Over the course of five social occasions, a committed bachelor must consider the notion that he may have discovered love.

Title: 3720. Sicario: Day of the Soldado
Short Description: The drug war on the U.S.-Mexico border has escalated as the cartels have begun trafficking terrorists across the US border. To fight the war, federal agent Matt Graver re-teams with the mercurial Alejandro.

Title: 3721. The Ring
Short Description: A journalist must investigate a mysterious videotape which seems to cause the death of anyone one week to the day after they view it.

Title: 3722. Furious 7
Short Description: Deckard Shaw seeks revenge against Dominic Toretto and his family for his comatose brother.

Title: 3723. Uncle Buck
Short Description: Laid back commitment-phobe Buck babysits his brother's rebellious teenage daughter and her cute younger brother and sister.

Title: 3724. Everest
Short Description: On May 10, 1996, mountain guides Rob Hall and Scott Fischer combine their expedition teams for a final ascent to the summit of Mount Everest. With little warning, a storm strikes the mountain and the climbers must now battle to survive.

Title: 3725. Pirates of the Caribbean: At World's End
Short Description: Will Turner, Elizabeth Swann, Hector Barbossa, and the crew of the Black Pearl try and rescue Jack from davy jones locker and prepare to fight Lord Cutler Beckett, who controls Davy Jones and the Flying Dutchman.

Title: 3726. The French Dispatch
Short Description: A love letter to journalists set in an outpost of an American newspaper in a fictional twentieth century French city, that brings to life a collection of stories published in "The French Dispatch Magazine".

Title: 3727. The Unforgivable
Short Description: A woman is released from prison after serving a sentence for a violent crime and re-enters a society that refuses to forgive her past.

Title: 3728. Escape from New York
Short Description: In 1997, when the U.S. president crashes into Manhattan, now a giant maximum security prison, a convicted bank robber is sent in to rescue him.

Title: 3729. The Intern
Short Description: Seventy-year-old widower Ben Whittaker has discovered that retirement isn't all it's cracked up to be. Seizing an opportunity to get back in the game, he becomes a senior intern at an online fashion site, founded and run by Jules Ostin.

Title: 3730. Dogtooth
Short Description: A controlling, manipulative father locks his three adult offsprings in a state of perpetual childhood by keeping them prisoner within the sprawling family compound.

Title: 3731. No Way Out
Short Description: A coverup and witchhunt occur after a politician accidentally kills his mistress.

Title: 3732. Batman Returns
Short Description: While Batman deals with a deformed man calling himself the Penguin wreaking havoc across Gotham with the help of a cruel businessman, a female employee of the latter becomes the Catwoman with her own vendetta.

Title: 3733. Vicky Cristina Barcelona
Short Description: Two friends on a summer holiday in Spain become enamored with the same painter, unaware that his ex-wife, with whom he has a tempestuous relationship, is about to re-enter the picture.

Title: 3734. Enchanted
Short Description: A young maiden in a land called Andalasia, who is prepared to be wed, is sent away to New York City by an evil Queen, where she falls in love with a lawyer.

Title: 3735. I, Robot
Short Description: In 2035, a technophobic cop investigates a crime that may have been perpetrated by a robot, which leads to a larger threat to humanity.

Title: 3736. The Master
Short Description: A Naval veteran arrives home from war unsettled and uncertain of his future - until he is tantalized by a cult and its charismatic leader.

Title: 3737. Die Hard 2
Short Description: John McClane attempts to avert disaster as rogue military operatives seize control of Dulles International Airport in Washington, D.C.

Title: 3738. Heathers
Short Description: At Westerburg High where cliques rule, jocks dominate and all the popular girls are named Heather, it's going to take a Veronica and mysterious new kid to give teen angst a body count.

Title: 3739. Love, Rosie
Short Description: Rosie and Alex have been best friends since they were 5, so they couldn't possibly be right for one another...or could they? When it comes to love, life and making the right choices, these two are their own worst enemies.

Title: 3740. Anchorman: The Legend of Ron Burgundy
Short Description: In the 1970s, an anchorman's stint as San Diego's top-rated newsreader is challenged when an ambitious newswoman becomes his co-anchor.

Title: 3741. Tangerine
Short Description: A hooker tears through Tinseltown on Christmas Eve searching for the pimp who broke her heart.

Title: 3742. Mean Creek
Short Description: When a teen is bullied, his brother and friends lure the bully into the woods to seek revenge.

Title: 3743. An Officer and a Gentleman
Short Description: A young man must complete his work at a Navy Officer Candidate School to become an aviator, with the help of a tough Gunnery Sergeant and his new girlfriend.

Title: 3744. Anastasia
Short Description: The last surviving child of the Russian Royal Family joins two con men to reunite with her grandmother, the Dowager Empress, while the undead Rasputin seeks her death.

Title: 3745. American Made
Short Description: The story of Barry Seal, an American pilot who became a drug-runner for the CIA in the 1980s in a clandestine operation that would be exposed as the Iran-Contra Affair.

Title: 3746. Shiva Baby
Short Description: While at a Jewish funeral service with her parents, a college student has an awkward encounter with her sugar daddy and ex-girlfriend.

Title: 3747. Elf
Short Description: Raised as an oversized elf, Buddy travels from the North Pole to New York City to meet his biological father, Walter Hobbs, who doesn't know he exists and is in desperate need of some Christmas spirit.

Title: 3748. WarGames
Short Description: A young man finds a back door into a military central computer in which reality is confused with game-playing, possibly starting World War III.

Title: 3749. Deja Vu
Short Description: After a ferry is bombed in New Orleans, an A.T.F. agent joins a unique investigation using experimental surveillance technology to find the bomber, but soon finds himself becoming obsessed with one of the victims.

Title: 3750. Live Free or Die Hard
Short Description: John McClane and a young hacker join forces to take down master cyber-terrorist Thomas Gabriel in Washington D.C.

Title: 3751. Never Let Me Go
Short Description: The lives of three friends, from their early school days into young adulthood, when the reality of the world they live in comes knocking.

Title: 3752. Remember Me
Short Description: A romantic drama centred on two new lovers: Tyler, whose parents have split in the wake of his brother's suicide, and Ally, who lives each day to the fullest since witnessing her mother's murder.

Title: 3753. The Danish Girl
Short Description: A fictitious love story loosely inspired by the lives of Danish artists Lili Elbe and Gerda Wegener. Lili and Gerda's marriage and work evolve as they navigate Lili's groundbreaking journey as a transgender pioneer.

Title: 3754. Parenthood
Short Description: Four Buckman siblings attempt to raise their children - each in their own different style - and deal with the joys and sorrows that the process brings.

Title: 3755. Dredd
Short Description: In a violent, futuristic city where the police have the authority to act as judge, jury and executioner, a cop teams with a trainee to take down a gang that deals the reality-altering drug, SLO-MO.

Title: 3756. Tommy Boy
Short Description: After his auto-parts tycoon father dies, the overweight, underachieving son teams up with a snide accountant to try and save the family business.

Title: 3757. Little Shop of Horrors
Short Description: A nerdy florist finds his chance for success and romance with the help of a giant man-eating plant who demands to be fed.

Title: 3758. War Dogs
Short Description: Loosely based on the true story of two young men, David Packouz and Efraim Diveroli, who won a three hundred million dollar contract from the Pentagon to arm America's allies in Afghanistan.

Title: 3759. Seven Psychopaths
Short Description: A struggling screenwriter inadvertently becomes entangled in the Los Angeles criminal underworld after his oddball friends kidnap a gangster's beloved Shih Tzu.

Title: 3760. Better Off Dead
Short Description: After his girlfriend Beth Truss ditches him for boorish ski jock Roy Stalin, sad-sack high-school student Lane Meyer decides that suicide is the only answer, but his inept attempts bring him nothing but agony and embarrassment.

Title: 3761. Out of Africa
Short Description: In 20th-century colonial Kenya, a Danish baroness/plantation owner has a passionate love affair with a free-spirited big-game hunter.

Title: 3762. The Witch: Part 1 - The Subversion
Short Description: When a bright high school student with memory loss enters a national talent show to help her struggling family, she finds her ordinary life flipped upside down by the sudden arrival of mysterious strangers seemingly connected to her past.

Title: 3763. The Goat Life
Short Description: An Indian man seeking work follows a job lead to Saudi Arabia, only to find himself forced to labor without pay as a goat herder in the remote desert.

Title: 3764. Dressed to Kill
Short Description: A mysterious blonde woman kills one of a psychiatrist's patients, and then goes after the high-class call girl who witnessed the murder.

Title: 3765. The Year of Living Dangerously
Short Description: A young Australian reporter tries to navigate the political turmoil of Indonesia during the rule of President Sukarno with the help of a diminutive photographer.

Title: 3766. Ever After: A Cinderella Story
Short Description: The Brothers Grimm arrive at the home of a wealthy Grande Dame who speaks of the many legends surrounding the fable of the cinder girl before telling the "true" story of her ancestor.

Title: 3767. Desperado
Short Description: Former musician and gunslinger El Mariachi arrives at a small Mexican border town after being away for a long time. His past quickly catches up with him and he soon gets entangled with the local drug kingpin Bucho and his gang.

Title: 3768. The Tragedy of Macbeth
Short Description: A Scottish lord becomes convinced by a trio of witches that he will become the next King of Scotland, and his ambitious wife supports him in his plans of seizing power.

Title: 3769. Payback
Short Description: After a successful heist, Porter is left for dead. Once he recovers, he seeks vengeance and wants his share of the money.

Title: 3770. Audition
Short Description: A widower takes an offer to screen girls at a special audition, arranged for him by a friend to find him a new wife. The one he fancies is not who she appears to be after all.

Title: 3771. Chicken Run
Short Description: When a cockerel apparently flies into a chicken farm, the chickens see him as an opportunity to escape their evil owners.

Title: 3772. Booksmart
Short Description: On the eve of their high-school graduation, two academic superstars and best friends realize they should have worked less and played more. Determined not to fall short of their peers, the girls try to cram four years of fun into one night.

Title: 3773. Mrs. Harris Goes to Paris
Short Description: In 1950s London, a widowed cleaning lady falls madly in love with a couture Dior dress, deciding she must have one. She embarks on an adventure to Paris that will change not only her own outlook -- but the very future of the House of Dior.

Title: 3774. The Big Chill
Short Description: A group of seven former college friends gather for a weekend reunion at a South Carolina vacation home after the funeral of another of their college friends.

Title: 3775. Definitely, Maybe
Short Description: A political consultant tries to explain his impending divorce and past relationships to his 11-year-old daughter.

Title: 3776. Bad Education
Short Description: The beloved superintendent of New York's Roslyn school district and his staff, friends and relatives become the prime suspects in the unfolding of the single largest public school embezzlement scandal in American history.

Title: 3777. Wild
Short Description: A chronicle of one woman's 1,100-mile solo hike undertaken as a way to recover from a recent personal tragedy.

Title: 3778. Valkyrie
Short Description: A dramatization of the July 20, 1944 assassination and political coup plot by desperate renegade German Army officers against Adolf Hitler during World War II.

Title: 3779. A Good Person
Short Description: Follows Allison, whose life falls apart following her involvement in a fatal accident.

Title: 3780. Kung Fu Panda 3
Short Description: Continuing his "legendary adventures of awesomeness", Po must face two hugely epic, but different threats: one supernatural and the other a little closer to home.

Title: 3781. The Square
Short Description: A prestigious Stockholm museum's chief art curator finds himself in times of both professional and personal crisis as he attempts to set up a controversial new exhibit.

Title: 3782. Shakespeare in Love
Short Description: The world's greatest ever playwright, William Shakespeare, is young, out of ideas and short of cash, but meets his ideal woman and is inspired to write one of his most famous plays.

Title: 3783. The Burial
Short Description: Inspired by true events, a lawyer helps a funeral home owner save his family business from a corporate behemoth, exposing a complex web of race, power, and injustice.

Title: 3784. Winter's Bone
Short Description: An unflinching Ozark Mountain girl hacks through dangerous social terrain as she hunts down her drug-dealing father while trying to keep her family intact.

Title: 3785. Brawl in Cell Block 99
Short Description: A former boxer-turned-drug runner lands in a prison battleground after a deal gets deadly.

Title: 3786. Allied
Short Description: In 1942, a Canadian intelligence officer in North Africa encounters a female French Resistance fighter on a deadly mission behind enemy lines. When they reunite in London, their relationship is tested by the pressures of war.

Title: 3787. Missing
Short Description: When her mother disappears while on vacation in Colombia with her new boyfriend, June's search for answers is hindered by international red tape. However, as she digs deeper, her digital sleuthing soon raises more questions than answers.

Title: 3788. Michael Collins
Short Description: Neil Jordan's historical biopic of Irish revolutionary Michael Collins, the man who led a guerrilla war against the UK, helped negotiate the creation of the Irish Free State, and led the National Army during the Irish Civil War.

Title: 3789. The Call
Short Description: Two people live in different times. Seo-Yeon lives in the present and Young-Sook lives in the past. One phone call connects the two, and their lives are changed irrevocably.

Title: 3790. In the Mouth of Madness
Short Description: An insurance investigator begins discovering that the impact a horror writer's books have on his fans is more than inspirational.

Title: 3791. The Time Traveler's Wife
Short Description: Henry DeTamble, a librarian, possesses a unique gene that lets him involuntarily travel through time. His wife, Claire Abshire, finds it difficult to cope with it.

Title: 3792. The Aristocats
Short Description: With the help of a smooth talking tomcat, a family of Parisian felines set to inherit a fortune from their owner try to make it back home after a jealous butler kidnaps them and leaves them in the country.

Title: 3793. Side Effects
Short Description: A young woman's world unravels when a drug prescribed by her psychiatrist has unexpected side effects.

Title: 3794. Alive
Short Description: After crash-landing in the snowswept Andes, a Uruguayan rugby team has no choice but to turn to desperate measures in order to survive.

Title: 3795. Cube
Short Description: A group of strangers awaken to find themselves placed in a giant cube. Each one of them is gifted with a special skill and they must work together to escape an endless maze of deadly traps.

Title: 3796. Don't Look Now
Short Description: A married couple grieving the recent death of their young daughter are in Venice when they encounter two elderly sisters, one of whom is psychic and brings a warning from beyond.

Title: 3797. On the Basis of Sex
Short Description: The true story of Ruth Bader Ginsburg, her struggles for equal rights, and the early cases of a historic career that lead to her nomination and confirmation as U.S. Supreme Court Associate Justice.

Title: 3798. The Dark Crystal
Short Description: On another planet in the distant past, a Gelfling embarks on a quest to find the missing shard of a magical crystal, and to restore order to his world.

Title: 3799. The Host
Short Description: A monster emerges from Seoul's Han River and begins attacking people. One victim's loving family does what it can to rescue her from its clutches.

Title: 3800. DC League of Super-Pets
Short Description: Krypto the Super-Dog and Superman are inseparable best friends, sharing the same superpowers and fighting crime side by side in Metropolis. However, Krypto must master his own powers for a rescue mission when Superman is kidnapped.

Title: 3801. Defiance
Short Description: Jewish brothers in German-occupied Eastern Europe escape into a Belorussian forest, where they join Russian resistance fighters, and endeavor to build a village, in order to protect themselves and about one thousand Jewish non-combatants.

Title: 3802. Phone Booth
Short Description: Publicist Stuart Shepard finds himself trapped in a phone booth, pinned down by an extortionist's sniper rifle. Unable to leave or receive outside help, Stuart's negotiation with the caller leads to a jaw-dropping climax.

Title: 3803. The Jerk
Short Description: A simpleminded, sheltered country boy suddenly decides to leave his family home to experience life in the big city, where his naivete is both his best friend and his worst enemy.

Title: 3804. The Poseidon Adventure
Short Description: A group of passengers must embark on a harrowing struggle for survival after a rogue wave capsizes their cruise ship at sea.

Title: 3805. The King of Staten Island
Short Description: Scott has been a case of arrested development since his firefighter dad died. He spends his days smoking weed and dreaming of being a tattoo artist until events force him to grapple with his grief and take his first steps forward in life.

Title: 3806. Runaway Jury
Short Description: A juror on the inside and a woman on the outside manipulate a court trial involving a major gun manufacturer.

Title: 3807. T2 Trainspotting
Short Description: After 20 years abroad, Mark Renton returns to Scotland and reunites with his old friends Sick Boy, Spud, and Begbie.

Title: 3808. Beautiful Girls
Short Description: A piano player at a crossroads in his life returns home to his friends and their own problems with life and love.

Title: 3809. John Q
Short Description: John Quincy Archibald takes a hospital emergency room hostage when his insurance won't cover his son's heart transplant.

Title: 3810. The Accused
Short Description: After a young woman suffers a brutal gang rape in a bar one night, a prosecutor assists in bringing the perpetrators to justice, including the ones who encouraged and cheered on the attack.

Title: 3811. Sector 36
Short Description: A fictional story Inspired by true events, several children go missing from a basti (slum) in Sector 36. A determined police officer must now face off with a cunning serial killer as a chilling investigation and dark secrets unfold.

Title: 3812. Locke
Short Description: Ivan Locke, a dedicated family man and successful construction manager, receives a phone call that sets in motion a series of events that threaten his carefully cultivated existence.

Title: 3813. American Underdog
Short Description: The story of NFL MVP and Hall of Fame quarterback Kurt Warner, who went from stocking shelves at a supermarket to becoming an American Football star.

Title: 3814. Thirst
Short Description: Through a failed medical experiment, a priest is stricken with vampirism and is forced to abandon his ascetic ways.

Title: 3815. Let Me In
Short Description: A bullied young boy befriends a young female vampire who lives in secrecy with her guardian.

Title: 3816. The Forgotten Battle
Short Description: In WWII's final years, a soldier in the German army, a British glider pilot, and a Dutch resistance fighter's paths intertwine. Their choices shape destinies, impacting not only their freedom but also that of others.

Title: 3817. Rocky Balboa
Short Description: Thirty years after the ring of the first bell, Rocky Balboa comes out of retirement and dons his gloves for his final fight against the reigning heavyweight champ Mason 'The Line' Dixon.

Title: 3818. Nowhere Boy
Short Description: A chronicle of John Lennon's first years, focused mainly in his adolescence and his relationship with his stern aunt Mimi, who raised him, and his absentee mother Julia, who re-entered his life at a crucial moment in his young life.

Title: 3819. Leave No Trace
Short Description: A father and his seventeen-year-old daughter are living an ideal existence in a vast urban park in Portland, Oregon when a small mistake derails their lives forever.

Title: 3820. Elephant
Short Description: Several ordinary high school students go through their daily routine as two others prepare for something more malevolent.

Title: 3821. The Glass Castle
Short Description: A young girl comes of age in a dysfunctional family of nonconformist nomads with a mother who's an eccentric artist and an alcoholic father who would stir the children's imagination with hope as a distraction to their poverty.

Title: 3822. The Dig
Short Description: An archaeologist embarks on the historically important excavation of Sutton Hoo in 1938.

Title: 3823. The Croods
Short Description: In the primeval era, Grug and his family risk the dangers of their surroundings to find a new dwelling place. Along the way, they meet a modern boy who woos them with his adventurous ways.

Title: 3824. Far from the Madding Crowd
Short Description: In Victorian England, the independent and headstrong Bathsheba Everdene attracts three very different suitors: Gabriel Oak, a sheep farmer; Frank Troy, a reckless Sergeant; and William Boldwood, a prosperous and mature bachelor.

Title: 3825. Nyad
Short Description: The remarkable true story of athlete Diana Nyad who, at the age of 60 and with the help of her best friend and coach, commits to achieving her life-long dream: a 110-mile open ocean swim from Cuba to Florida.

Title: 3826. The Muppets
Short Description: A Muppet fanatic with some help from his 2 human compatriots must regroup the Muppet gang to stop an avaricious oil mogul from taking down one of their precious life-longing treasures.

Title: 3827. Black Christmas
Short Description: During their Christmas break, a group of sorority girls are stalked by a stranger.

Title: 3828. Miracles from Heaven
Short Description: Based on the incredible true story of the Beam family.

Title: 3829. Bedknobs and Broomsticks
Short Description: An apprentice witch, three kids, and a cynical magician conman search for the missing component to a magic spell to be used in the defense of Britain in World War II.

Title: 3830. Sneakers
Short Description: A security pro finds his past returning to haunt him when he and his unique team are tasked with retrieving a particularly important item.

Title: 3831. Seven Years in Tibet
Short Description: Heinrich Harrer, an Austrian climber, breaks out of prison and travels to the holy city of Lhasa. He is employed as an instructor to the 14th Dalai Lama and soon becomes his close confidante.

Title: 3832. Blue Ruin
Short Description: A mysterious outsider's quiet life is turned upside down when he returns to his childhood home to carry out an act of vengeance. Proving himself an amateur assassin, he winds up in a brutal fight to protect his estranged family.

Title: 3833. The Seven Year Itch
Short Description: When his family goes away for the summer, a hitherto faithful husband with an overactive imagination is tempted by a beautiful neighbor.

Title: 3834. Creed II
Short Description: Under the tutelage of Rocky Balboa, newly crowned heavyweight champion Adonis Creed faces off against Viktor Drago, the son of Ivan Drago.

Title: 3835. The Frighteners
Short Description: After a tragic car accident that kills his wife, a man discovers he can communicate with the dead, and he uses that gift to con people. However, when a demonic spirit appears, he may be the only one who can stop it from killing the living and the dead.

Title: 3836. Chariots of Fire
Short Description: Two British track athletes, one a determined Jew and the other a devout Christian, are driven to win in the 1924 Olympics as they wrestle with issues of pride and conscience.

Title: 3837. Benny & Joon
Short Description: A mentally ill young woman finds her love in an eccentric man who models himself after Buster Keaton.

Title: 3838. Spy Game
Short Description: Retiring CIA agent Nathan Muir recalls his training of Tom Bishop while working against agency politics to free him from his Chinese captors.

Title: 3839. Three Kings
Short Description: In the aftermath of the Persian Gulf War, four soldiers set out to steal gold that was stolen from Kuwait, but they discover people who desperately need their help.

Title: 3840. Lords of Dogtown
Short Description: The film follows the surf and skateboarding trends that originated in Venice, California during the 1970s.

Title: 3841. God's Crooked Lines
Short Description: Follows a woman checking into a psychiatric ward to investigate a homicide.

Title: 3842. Wag the Dog
Short Description: Shortly before an election, a spin-doctor and a Hollywood producer join efforts to fabricate a war in order to cover up a Presidential sex scandal.

Title: 3843. A Tale of Two Sisters
Short Description: After being institutionalized in a mental hospital, Su-mi reunites with her sister, Su-yeon, and they return to live at their country home. But strange events plague the house, leading to surprising revelations and a shocking conclusion.

Title: 3844. One-Eyed Jacks
Short Description: After they rob a bank in Mexico, Dad Longworth absconds with the loot leaving his partner, Rio, to be captured by the Rurales. 5 years later, Rio escapes from prison and seeks revenge on Longworth, but falls in love with his step-daughter.

Title: 3845. Elle
Short Description: A successful businesswoman gets caught up in a game of cat and mouse as she tracks down the unknown man who raped her.

Title: 3846. The Adventures of Baron Munchausen
Short Description: An account of Baron Munchausen's supposed travels and fantastical experiences across late 18th-century Europe with his band of misfits.

Title: 3847. First Reformed
Short Description: A minister of a small congregation in upstate New York grapples with mounting despair brought on by tragedy, worldly concerns and a tormented past.

Title: 3848. Hardcore
Short Description: A religious businessman from Michigan has to venture into the world of pornography in California, desperately searching for his runaway teenage daughter.

Title: 3849. The Longest Yard
Short Description: A sadistic warden asks a former pro quarterback, now serving time in his prison, to put together a team of inmates to take on (and get pummeled by) the guards.

Title: 3850. Yours, Mine and Ours
Short Description: A widower with ten children falls for a widow with eight, and they must decide about forming a huge, unconventional family.

Title: 3851. Rumble Fish
Short Description: Absent-minded street thug Rusty James struggles to live up to his legendary older brother's reputation, and longs for the days of gang warfare.

Title: 3852. Balto
Short Description: An outcast Husky risks his life with other sled dogs to prevent a deadly epidemic from ravaging Nome, Alaska.

Title: 3853. Sick of Myself
Short Description: Increasingly overshadowed by her boyfriend's recent rise to fame as a sculptor of stolen furniture, Signe hatches a vicious plan to reclaim her rightfully deserved attention within the milieu of Oslo's cultural elite.

Title: 3854. Kinsey
Short Description: A look at the life of Alfred Kinsey, a pioneer in the area of human sexuality research, whose 1948 publication "Sexual Behavior in the Human Male" was one of the first recorded works that saw science address sexual behavior.

Title: 3855. Hatari!
Short Description: A group of men trap wild animals in Africa and sell them to zoos before the arrival of a female wildlife photographer threatens to change their ways.

Title: 3856. The Jacket
Short Description: A Gulf war veteran is wrongly sent to a mental institution for insane criminals, where he becomes the object of a doctor's experiments, and his life is completely affected by them.

Title: 3857. Megan Leavey
Short Description: Based on the true life story of a young Marine corporal whose unique discipline and bond with her military combat dog saved many lives during their deployment in Iraq.

Title: 3858. State of Play
Short Description: When a congressional aide is killed, a Washington, D.C. journalist starts investigating the case involving the Representative, his old college friend.

Title: 3859. Re-Animator
Short Description: After an odd new medical student arrives on campus, a dedicated local and his girlfriend become involved in bizarre experiments centering around the re-animation of dead tissue.

Title: 3860. Flags of Our Fathers
Short Description: The life stories of the six men who raised the flag at the Battle of Iwo Jima, a turning point in World War II.

Title: 3861. Guys and Dolls
Short Description: In New York, a gambler is challenged to take a cold female missionary to Havana, but they fall for each other, and the bet has a hidden motive to finance a crap game.

Title: 3862. Day of the Dead
Short Description: As the world is overrun by zombies, a group of scientists and military personnel sheltering in an underground bunker in Florida must decide on how they should deal with the undead horde.

Title: 3863. The Swimming Pool
Short Description: Jean-Paul and Marianne spend lazy holidays at their villa in idyllic Southern France. However when Harry and his attractive young daughter Penelope show up, the dreamy summer days are suddenly filled with unspoken tension and jealousy.

Title: 3864. Brick
Short Description: A teenage loner pushes his way into the underworld of a high school crime ring to investigate the disappearance of his ex-girlfriend.

Title: 3865. Human Traffic
Short Description: Five youngsters embrace the 90s clubbing scene on a drug-fuelled weekend of partying in Cardiff.

Title: 3866. Catch-22
Short Description: A military pilot makes a valiant effort to be certified insane during World War II so that he can be excused from flying missions. But there's a catch.

Title: 3867. Agora
Short Description: A historical drama set in Roman Egypt, concerning a slave who turns to the rising tide of Christianity in the hope of pursuing freedom while falling in love with his mistress, the philosophy and mathematics professor Hypatia of Alexandria.

Title: 3868. Gentlemen Prefer Blondes
Short Description: Showgirls Lorelei Lee and Dorothy Shaw travel to Paris, pursued by a private detective hired by the suspicious father of Lorelei's fiancé, as well as a rich, enamored old man and many other doting admirers.

Title: 3869. The Pink Panther Strikes Again
Short Description: After escaping from an insane asylum, the bonkers Charles Dreyfus sends 26 assassins on the trail of the forever bumbling Inspector Clouseau.

Title: 3870. How the West Was Won
Short Description: A family saga covering several decades of Westward expansion in the 19th century, including the Gold Rush, the Civil War, and the building of the railroads.

Title: 3871. Gridiron Gang
Short Description: Teenagers at a juvenile detention center, under the leadership of their counselor, gain self-esteem by playing football together.

Title: 3872. Ron's Gone Wrong
Short Description: The story of Barney, an awkward middle-schooler and Ron, his new walking, talking, digitally-connected device. Ron's malfunctions set against the backdrop of the social media age launch them on a journey to learn about true friendship.

Title: 3873. The Sword in the Stone
Short Description: A poor boy named Arthur learns the power of love, kindness, knowledge and bravery with the help of a wizard called Merlin in the path to become one of the most beloved kings in English history.

Title: 3874. Swiss Family Robinson
Short Description: A Swiss family must survive being shipwrecked on a deserted island.

Title: 3875. Casualties of War
Short Description: During the Vietnam War, a soldier finds himself the outsider of his own squad when they unnecessarily kidnap a female villager, for their sexual enjoyment.

Title: 3876. The Cat Returns
Short Description: After helping a cat, a seventeen-year-old girl finds herself involuntarily engaged to a cat Prince in a magical world where her only hope of freedom lies with a dapper cat statuette come to life.

Title: 3877. The Kings of Summer
Short Description: Three teenage friends, in the ultimate act of independence, decide to spend their summer building a house in the woods and living off the land.

Title: 3878. Silkwood
Short Description: A worker at a plutonium processing plant is purposefully contaminated, psychologically tortured and possibly murdered to prevent her from exposing worker safety violations at the plant.

Title: 3879. Timecrimes
Short Description: A man accidentally gets into a time machine and travels back in time nearly an hour. Finding himself will be the first of a series of disasters of unforeseeable consequences.

Title: 3880. 5 to 7
Short Description: An aspiring novelist enters into a relationship with a woman, though there's just one catch: She's married and the couple can only meet between the hours of 5 and 7 each evening.

Title: 3881. Nicholas Nickleby
Short Description: A young, compassionate man struggles to save his family and friends from the abusive exploitation of his cold-heartedly grasping uncle.

Title: 3882. Big Jake
Short Description: In 1909, when John Fain's gang kidnaps Jacob McCandles' grandson and holds him for ransom, Big Jake sets out to rescue the boy.

Title: 3883. Crossroads
Short Description: A wannabe blues-guitar virtuoso finds an old blues player and hopes he can teach him a long-lost song by legendary musician, Robert Johnson.

Title: 3884. Like Water for Chocolate
Short Description: When tradition prevents her from marrying the man she loves, a young woman discovers she has a unique talent for cooking.

Title: 3885. McLintock!
Short Description: Wealthy rancher G. W. McLintock uses his power and influence in the territory to keep the peace between farmers, ranchers, land-grabbers, Indians and corrupt government officials.

Title: 3886. Hard Eight
Short Description: Professional gambler Sydney teaches John the tricks of the trade. John does well until he falls for cocktail waitress Clementine.

Title: 3887. The World According to Garp
Short Description: A struggling young writer finds his life and work dominated by his unfaithful wife and his radical feminist mother, whose best-selling manifesto turns her into a cultural icon.

Title: 3888. Klute
Short Description: A small-town detective searching for a missing man has only one lead: a connection with a New York prostitute.

Title: 3889. The Changeling
Short Description: After experiencing tragic personal losses, a music professor rents a Seattle mansion, haunted by a slain boy.

Title: 3890. Jesus Revolution
Short Description: The true story of a national spiritual awakening in the early 1970s and its origins within a community of teenage hippies in Southern California.

Title: 3891. The Three Musketeers
Short Description: A young swordsman comes to Paris and faces villains, romance, adventure and intrigue with three Musketeer friends.

Title: 3892. Orlando
Short Description: After Queen Elizabeth I commands him not to grow old, a young nobleman struggles with love and his place in the world.

Title: 3893. Breathe
Short Description: The inspiring true love story of Robin and Diana Cavendish, an adventurous couple who refuse to give up in the face of a devastating disease.

Title: 3894. Broken Flowers
Short Description: As the extremely withdrawn Don Johnston is dumped by his latest woman, he receives an anonymous letter from a former lover informing him that he has a son who may be looking for him. A freelance sleuth neighbor moves Don to embark on a cross-country search for his old flames in search of answers.

Title: 3895. Carnage
Short Description: Two pairs of parents hold a cordial meeting after their sons are involved in a fight, though as their time together progresses, increasingly childish behavior throws the discussion into chaos.

Title: 3896. Ong-Bak: The Thai Warrior
Short Description: When the head of a statue sacred to a village is stolen, a young martial artist goes to the big city and finds himself taking on the underworld to retrieve it.

Title: 3897. North Sea Texas
Short Description: A teenage boy's search for love finds him fixated on a boy who lives nearby.

Title: 3898. Winnie the Pooh
Short Description: While searching for honey, Pooh and his friends embark on an adventure to find Eeyore's missing tail and rescue Christopher Robin from an unknown monster called The Backson.

Title: 3899. Marnie
Short Description: Mark marries Marnie although she is a habitual thief and has serious psychological problems, and tries to help her confront and resolve them.

Title: 3900. Parallel Mothers
Short Description: The story of two mothers who bond in unexpected way after giving birth the same day.

Title: 3901. The Thing from Another World
Short Description: Scientists and American Air Force officials fend off a bloodthirsty alien organism while at a remote arctic outpost.

Title: 3902. Vettaiyan
Short Description: Ruthless criminal activity is met with force from a maverick police officer with a disregard for the rules as he confronts an outbreak of lawlessness.

Title: 3903. The Girl Who Played with Fire
Short Description: As computer hacker Lisbeth and journalist Mikael investigate a sex-trafficking ring, Lisbeth is accused of three murders, causing her to go on the run while Mikael works to clear her name.

Title: 3904. The Panic in Needle Park
Short Description: Follows the lives of heroin addicts who frequent "Needle Park" in New York City.

Title: 3905. If Beale Street Could Talk
Short Description: A young woman embraces her pregnancy while she and her family set out to prove her childhood friend and lover innocent of a crime he didn't commit.

Title: 3906. The Great Mouse Detective
Short Description: Basil, the rodent Sherlock Holmes, investigates the kidnapping of a toy maker and uncovers its link to his archenemy, Professor Ratigan.

Title: 3907. The Dark Valley
Short Description: Through a hidden path, a lone rider reaches a little town high up in the Alps. Nobody knows where the stranger comes from, nor what he wants there. But everyone knows that they don't want him to stay.

Title: 3908. Gunfight at the O.K. Corral
Short Description: Lawman Wyatt Earp and outlaw Doc Holliday form an unlikely alliance which culminates in their participation in the legendary Gunfight at the O.K. Corral.

Title: 3909. White Oleander
Short Description: A teenager journeys through a series of foster homes after her mother goes to prison for committing a crime of passion.

Title: 3910. Broker
Short Description: When a young mother reconsiders abandoning her baby, she discovers a scheme selling foundlings for adoption.

Title: 3911. The Old Oak
Short Description: The future for the last remaining pub, The Old Oak, in a village of Northeast England, where people are leaving the land as the mines are closed. Houses are cheap and available, thus making it an ideal location for Syrian refugees.

Title: 3912. Chopper
Short Description: Chopper tells the intense story of Mark "Chopper" Read, a legendary criminal who wrote his autobiography while serving a jail sentence in prison. His book, "From the Inside", upon which the film is based, was a best-seller.

Title: 3913. Queen & Slim
Short Description: A couple's first date takes an unexpected turn when a police officer pulls them over.

Title: 3914. Shattered Glass
Short Description: The story of a young journalist who fell from grace when it was discovered he fabricated over half of his articles from the publication The New Republic magazine.

Title: 3915. Southern Comfort
Short Description: During a routine exercise, a team of National Guardsmen are threatened by angry and violent locals.

Title: 3916. Half Nelson
Short Description: An inner-city junior high school teacher with a drug habit forms an unlikely friendship with one of his students after she discovers his secret.

Title: 3917. Belle
Short Description: Suzu is a shy high school student living in a rural village. For years, she has only been a shadow of herself. But when she enters "U", a massive virtual world, she escapes into her online persona as Belle, a globally-beloved singer.

Title: 3918. In Order of Disappearance
Short Description: After his son is murdered by drug dealers, a snowplow driver starts seeking revenge.

Title: 3919. Kinky Boots
Short Description: A drag queen comes to the rescue of a man who, after inheriting his father's shoe factory, needs to diversify his product if he wants to keep the business afloat.

Title: 3920. The Railway Man
Short Description: A former British Army officer, who was tortured as a prisoner of war at a Japanese labor camp during World War II, discovers that the man responsible for much of his treatment is still alive and sets out to confront him.

Title: 3921. Nitram
Short Description: Events leading up to the 1996 Port Arthur massacre on Tasmania in an attempt to understand why and how the atrocity occurred.

Title: 3922. Concussion
Short Description: In Pittsburgh, accomplished pathologist Dr. Bennet Omalu uncovers the truth about brain damage in football players who suffer repeated concussions in the course of normal play.

Title: 3923. Jailer
Short Description: A retired jailer goes on a manhunt to find his son's killers. But the road leads him to a familiar, albeit a bit darker place. Can he emerge from this complex situation successfully?

Title: 3924. The Chase
Short Description: The citizens of a small Texas town become worried and panicked when a local bad boy escapes prison and heads for his hometown.

Title: 3925. Night Moves
Short Description: Los Angeles private investigator Harry Moseby is hired by a client to find her runaway teenage daughter. Moseby tracks the daughter down, only to stumble upon something much more intriguing and sinister.

Title: 3926. Thursday
Short Description: A former L.A. drug dealer has moved to Houston to make a new life for himself as a married architect. Everything falls apart when he is suddenly visited by one of his former cohorts who comes carrying heroin.

Title: 3927. One False Move
Short Description: A small town police chief awaits the arrival of a gang of killers.

Title: 3928. Safe
Short Description: An affluent and unexceptional homemaker in the suburbs develops multiple chemical sensitivity.

Title: 3929. The Great Muppet Caper
Short Description: Kermit the Frog, The Great Gonzo, and Fozzie Bear are reporters who travel to Britain to interview a rich victim of jewel thieves and help her along with her secretary, Miss Piggy.

Title: 3930. Firebird
Short Description: Firebird follows a handsome, soulful young soldier who embarks on a clandestine sexual affair with a charismatic fighter pilot on a Soviet Air Force Base at the height of 1970's Communist rule.

Title: 3931. Chasing Mavericks
Short Description: When young Jay Moriarity discovers that the mythic Mavericks surf break, one of the biggest waves on Earth, exists just miles from his Santa Cruz home, he enlists the help of local legend Frosty Hesson to train him to survive it.

Title: 3932. The Bird with the Crystal Plumage
Short Description: An American writer vacationing in Rome attempts to unmask a serial killer he witnessed in the act of an attempted murder, and who is now hunting him and his girlfriend.

Title: 3933. My Bodyguard
Short Description: When Clifford Peache enrolls in a new high school and is harassed by a bully named Moody, he acquires the services of the school's most feared kid, the sullen Ricky Linderman, as a bodyguard.

Title: 3934. I'm Your Man
Short Description: In order to obtain research funds for her studies, a scientist accepts an offer to participate in an extraordinary experiment: for three weeks, she is to live with a humanoid robot, created to make her happy.

Title: 3935. The Driver
Short Description: A getaway driver becomes the latest assignment for a tenacious detective.

Title: 3936. Black Mirror: Bandersnatch
Short Description: A young programmer starts to question reality when he adapts a mad writer's fantasy novel into a video game.

Title: 3937. Whatever Works
Short Description: A middle-aged, misanthropic divorcé from New York City surprisingly enters a fulfilling, Pygmalion-type relationship with a much younger, unsophisticated Southern girl.

Title: 3938. Kon-Tiki
Short Description: In 1947, with five loyal friends in tow, explorer Thor Heyerdahl sails a fragile balsa wood raft along an ancient path some 4,300 miles across the Pacific.

Title: 3939. Barfly

Title: 3940. The Age of Shadows
Short Description: Korean resistance fighters smuggle explosives to destroy facilities controlled by Japanese forces in this period action thriller.

Title: 3941. Race

Title: 3944. Can You Ever Forgive Me?

Title: 3945. An American in Paris
Short Description: Three friends struggle to find work in Paris. Things become more complicated when two of them fall in love with the same woman.

Title: 3946. Dangerous Beauty

Title: 3947. To Leslie
Short Description: A single mother tries to reclaim her life and connection with her son after winning the lottery and spending all her money on parties and alcohol.

Title: 3948. Eye of the Needle

Title: 3949. Brubaker

Title: 3950. Titus
Short Description: Titus returns victorious from war, only to plant the seeds of future turmoil for himself and his family.

Title: 3951. On the Beach

Title: 3952. Drowning by Numbers

Title: 3953. Turkish Delight

Title: 3954. Cold Fish
Short Description: The lives of a bored suburban couple are changed forever when a seemingly nice old man gives their daughter a job at his fish store, and soon his gruesome hobbies are brought to light.

Title: 3955. It's Kind of a Funny Story
Short Description: A clinically-depressed teenager gets a new start after he checks himself into an adult psychiatric ward.

Title: 3956. The White Tiger
Short Description: An ambitious Indian driver uses his wit and cunning to escape from poverty and rise to the top. An epic journey based on the New York Times bestseller.

Title: 3957. Brother

Title: 3958. Gloria

Title: 3959. Three O'Clock High

Title: 3960. Koi... Mil Gaya
Short Description: A developmentally disabled young man tries to continue the work his father did in communicating with extra-terrestrials from outer space, which leads to something miraculous and wonderful.

Title: 3961. A Love Song for Bobby Long
Short Description: A headstrong young woman returns to New Orleans after the death of her estranged mother.

Title: 3962. Black Sunday

Short Description: The life of Cuban poet and novelist, Reinaldo Arenas.

Title: 3964. Nixon
Short Description: A biographical story of former U.S. President Richard Nixon, from his days as a young boy, to his eventual Presidency, which ended in shame.

Title: 3965. District B13

The events leading up to an 11:14 p.m. car crash, from five very different perspectives.

Title: 3969. American Me

Title: 3970. The Messenger

Title: 3971. Sleeper

Title: 3972. Venus in Fur

Title: 3973. The Parallax View

Title: 3976. Fearless
Short Description: A man's personality is dramatically changed after surviving a major airline crash.

Title: 3977. Mosul

Title: 3981. Department Q: The Absent One

Title: 3982. The Woodsman

Title: 3985. Aashiqui 2

Title: 3988. The Fly
Short Description: A scientist has a horrific accident when he tries to use his newly invented teleportation device.

Title: 3989. God Bless America

Title: 3990. Female Trouble

Title: 3996. The Big Red One

Title: 3997. Blood and Black Lace

Title: 4000. 45 Years
